1
00:00:01,790 --> 00:00:10,200
<b>Hotel Del Luna Blu-ray Disc 2</b>
Subtitle re-timing by Jharel

2
00:00:48,674 --> 00:00:50,014
<i>Are you alive?</i>

3
00:00:50,843 --> 00:00:51,973
<i>Or are you dead?</i>

4
00:00:53,763 --> 00:00:54,933
I'm just...

5
00:00:57,558 --> 00:00:58,598
here.

6
00:01:00,728 --> 00:01:02,978
<i>I'm neither alive</i>

7
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:06,610
<i>nor dead.</i>

8
00:01:07,777 --> 00:01:08,817
<i>I'm just stuck.</i>

9
00:01:10,112 --> 00:01:12,162
<i>I'm confined in a time zone</i>

10
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:15,743
<i>that can't ever be turned back.</i>

11
00:01:34,637 --> 00:01:35,637
Let's go!

12
00:02:16,762 --> 00:02:17,812
No!

13
00:04:21,929 --> 00:04:24,599
You're the one
that led the group, aren't you?

14
00:04:25,891 --> 00:04:26,981
You're the ringleader.

15
00:05:04,555 --> 00:05:05,555
Hey.

16
00:05:06,515 --> 00:05:08,385
You guys are thieves
from Gaori Village, aren't you?

17
00:05:08,976 --> 00:05:10,596
That means you're a nomad from Goguryeo.

18
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:13,110
You get what I'm saying, don't you?

19
00:05:14,064 --> 00:05:14,904
Hey!

20
00:05:15,316 --> 00:05:16,316
Shut it.

21
00:05:20,029 --> 00:05:22,359
I'm also from the same place.
Hello, brother.

22
00:05:22,614 --> 00:05:24,784
Or should I call you "sister"?

23
00:05:26,076 --> 00:05:26,906
"Sister"?

24
00:05:27,911 --> 00:05:28,751
Sister.

25
00:05:29,788 --> 00:05:31,288
Why don't you let me free now?

26
00:05:50,309 --> 00:05:53,269
I'm just a low-class officer
in charge of escorting his superiors.

27
00:05:53,437 --> 00:05:55,687
So you won't get much money
by holding me hostage.

28
00:05:56,148 --> 00:05:57,518
I know how I'm going to get money.

29
00:05:57,649 --> 00:05:58,479
What?

30
00:05:58,859 --> 00:06:02,239
The noble lady who didn't even care
about losing her silk bundle

31
00:06:03,989 --> 00:06:05,869
seemed to care very dearly
about something else.

32
00:06:19,671 --> 00:06:23,591
I guess guarding the young lady wasn't
the only thing in your job description.

33
00:06:24,968 --> 00:06:28,428
All I did was talk with her a few times
so she wouldn't be bored on her way.

34
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:30,472
I guess she couldn't help

35
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:33,100
but fall for me
because of this pretty face.

36
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:37,654
Then your face must be worth quite a bit.

37
00:06:40,859 --> 00:06:42,529
Can I persuade you to let me go?

38
00:06:43,445 --> 00:06:45,275
If my hands and feet were free,

39
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:47,445
I'm sure I would be even more persuasive.

40
00:06:52,162 --> 00:06:54,582
If I cut off your tongue
for talking nonsense,

41
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:58,415
will the price for your face fall?

42
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:02,130
How can you say such a scary thing?

43
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:07,683
Darn.

44
00:07:42,337 --> 00:07:43,257
Pull me up.

45
00:07:45,424 --> 00:07:47,434
What are you doing? Can't you hear me?

46
00:07:47,509 --> 00:07:49,509
How can I help you when I'm like this?

47
00:07:50,554 --> 00:07:53,314
If my hands and feet were free,
I could help you better.

48
00:07:53,807 --> 00:07:54,887
Throw me your sword.

49
00:07:58,187 --> 00:08:00,647
Don't move. If you move,
you'll be sucked in faster.

50
00:08:04,401 --> 00:08:05,401
Throw me your sword.

51
00:08:35,557 --> 00:08:37,307
Where are you going?

52
00:08:38,101 --> 00:08:38,981
Come back!

53
00:09:09,007 --> 00:09:10,047
Grab it.

54
00:09:12,761 --> 00:09:13,601
Quickly!

55
00:09:29,444 --> 00:09:31,034
You're my hostage now.

56
00:09:31,697 --> 00:09:33,657
The price on my head would be much higher

57
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:36,703
than the price
on a low-class warrior's face.

58
00:09:39,746 --> 00:09:43,996
Actually, I'm not a low-class warrior.

59
00:09:45,377 --> 00:09:47,747
The lady I was escorting
is the princess of Yeongju Castle.

60
00:09:47,838 --> 00:09:50,298
And I'm the captain of her guards.

61
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:45,770
Are you looking at the moon
that has come up today?

62
00:10:45,854 --> 00:10:49,234
Or the moon that came up
a thousand years ago?

63
00:10:49,316 --> 00:10:51,396
They are all one and the same.

64
00:10:54,905 --> 00:10:59,195
The flowers in the garden
have blossomed brightly.

65
00:10:59,576 --> 00:11:01,696
You must have taken good care
of your guests so far

66
00:11:01,787 --> 00:11:04,077
at the Guest House of the Moon.

67
00:11:04,456 --> 00:11:06,746
I told you I changed
the name of this place.

68
00:11:07,209 --> 00:11:09,879
It's not a guest house.
It's Hotel del Luna.

69
00:11:11,129 --> 00:11:13,049
Stop calling me a landlady.

70
00:11:13,131 --> 00:11:14,341
I'm the president.

71
00:11:14,841 --> 00:11:16,391
They are the same thing.

72
00:11:17,594 --> 00:11:20,724
I saw that the human
who had served you for a while left you.

73
00:11:22,265 --> 00:11:25,635
Well, from death comes a new life.

74
00:11:26,937 --> 00:11:28,267
I also died.

75
00:11:30,148 --> 00:11:32,108
Why don't they take me?

76
00:11:32,359 --> 00:11:33,819
You didn't die.

77
00:11:34,736 --> 00:11:36,236
You are tied to the Moon Tree,

78
00:11:36,321 --> 00:11:39,531
and the flow of life and death
has stopped for you. I told you that.

79
00:11:39,658 --> 00:11:41,368
How long will you keep me tied up?

80
00:11:41,493 --> 00:11:44,003
It's you who is not budging.

81
00:11:44,538 --> 00:11:46,618
I shriveled up and died.

82
00:11:47,124 --> 00:11:49,334
If you cut it up and burn it,

83
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:50,999
I will be on my way.

84
00:11:52,754 --> 00:11:56,554
The leaves sprout,
and the flowers bloom and wither.

85
00:11:57,008 --> 00:12:00,468
The time of life and death
will flow once again.

86
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:06,184
Don't you think you should leave something
pretty like this behind before you go?

87
00:12:08,145 --> 00:12:11,435
I have nothing pretty and colorful
like that to leave behind.

88
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:15,192
Why don't you pick the bright flowers

89
00:12:15,277 --> 00:12:18,567
and give them to pitiful spirits
when you see them off?

90
00:12:26,371 --> 00:12:27,831
That child is still

91
00:12:28,832 --> 00:12:30,632
filled to the brim...

92
00:12:34,838 --> 00:12:38,588
I can't leave you like this forever.

93
00:14:27,075 --> 00:14:29,655
Thank you for saving me earlier.

94
00:14:29,744 --> 00:14:31,004
Consider yourself lucky.

95
00:14:31,746 --> 00:14:34,246
I wouldn't have saved you
if you had been wearing other shoes.

96
00:14:35,959 --> 00:14:38,879
They are so much better
than the tacky poop colored shoes.

97
00:14:38,962 --> 00:14:42,012
You waited for me,
wearing the shoes that I chose for you.

98
00:14:43,884 --> 00:14:44,934
I never waited for you.

99
00:14:45,010 --> 00:14:46,010
Come on.

100
00:14:46,803 --> 00:14:49,563
You sent me a text on the pretext
of that tiger, and waited for me.

101
00:14:49,639 --> 00:14:50,889
I was just curious.

102
00:14:50,974 --> 00:14:52,394
Of course you were curious.

103
00:14:52,726 --> 00:14:55,266
Because you've been
thinking about me all along.

104
00:14:55,687 --> 00:14:56,857
Did you

105
00:14:57,856 --> 00:14:59,896
cast a spell on me or something?

106
00:15:00,358 --> 00:15:01,898
Is that why I dreamed about you?

107
00:15:03,445 --> 00:15:04,645
You dreamed about me?

108
00:15:04,946 --> 00:15:07,366
Seeing ghosts like this
is already too much for me.

109
00:15:07,449 --> 00:15:09,329
I don't want to see you in my dream.

110
00:15:09,409 --> 00:15:12,199
Why? Did I eat you up
in your dream or something?

111
00:15:25,717 --> 00:15:26,757
Forget it.

112
00:15:27,218 --> 00:15:29,048
I don't think it was you in my dream.

113
00:15:29,137 --> 00:15:31,057
If she were you,
she wouldn't have done that.

114
00:15:33,975 --> 00:15:35,055
I forgive you.

115
00:15:38,355 --> 00:15:40,815
You are an adult,
so you can have a dream like that.

116
00:15:42,525 --> 00:15:43,605
What?

117
00:15:43,693 --> 00:15:44,903
It's not that kind of dream!

118
00:15:46,821 --> 00:15:50,451
Koo Chan-sung. I thought you were weak,

119
00:15:51,034 --> 00:15:52,874
but you are actually very healthy.

120
00:15:55,372 --> 00:15:57,292
Yes, I am very healthy.

121
00:15:57,374 --> 00:15:59,084
Okay, you stay healthy.

122
00:15:59,542 --> 00:16:02,842
If you faint like earlier again,
it will be too troublesome for me.

123
00:16:04,547 --> 00:16:06,127
How did you bring me here?

124
00:16:06,925 --> 00:16:08,885
Did you teleport me or something?

125
00:16:10,512 --> 00:16:11,472
It was nothing.

126
00:16:11,554 --> 00:16:13,524
Just like you brought a handcart
the other day,

127
00:16:13,848 --> 00:16:15,768
I brought something to carry you here.

128
00:16:21,439 --> 00:16:22,359
Get in there.

129
00:16:23,984 --> 00:16:25,034
Let's move him.

130
00:16:38,873 --> 00:16:40,793
Ms. Jang, I'm in him.

131
00:16:41,084 --> 00:16:42,094
Let's go.

132
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:44,880
Wait for me.

133
00:16:46,423 --> 00:16:49,183
Come on, Ms. Jang.

134
00:16:51,177 --> 00:16:52,177
Come out of there.

135
00:16:52,262 --> 00:16:53,762
Now that I'm in a human body,

136
00:16:53,847 --> 00:16:55,677
may I go out and party a little?

137
00:16:55,765 --> 00:16:56,675
Come out.

138
00:16:56,766 --> 00:16:58,806
I really don't want
to get out of this body.

139
00:16:58,893 --> 00:17:00,693
Ms. Jang. Please.

140
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:01,770
Come out!

141
00:17:11,614 --> 00:17:12,824
That must have hurt.

142
00:17:12,907 --> 00:17:13,777
Go.

143
00:17:15,285 --> 00:17:16,195
Go!

144
00:17:19,622 --> 00:17:22,672
<i>All you need to know is
that I moved you here safely.</i>

145
00:17:28,423 --> 00:17:31,053
Is your neck all right?

146
00:17:32,093 --> 00:17:33,093
Sure.

147
00:17:34,429 --> 00:17:35,429
Why?

148
00:17:36,097 --> 00:17:37,217
As long as you're fine.

149
00:17:37,974 --> 00:17:38,854
Let's go.

150
00:17:39,225 --> 00:17:41,185
Now that you're at my hotel,
I'll give you a tour.

151
00:17:48,735 --> 00:17:52,235
Does this place really exist
in the real world?

152
00:17:52,447 --> 00:17:53,817
Like I said last time,

153
00:17:53,907 --> 00:17:56,787
our hotel is officially registered
at the Jung-gu District Office,

154
00:17:56,868 --> 00:17:58,658
and we pay all the taxes too.

155
00:18:02,707 --> 00:18:04,667
<i>It does exist in the real world,</i>

156
00:18:04,959 --> 00:18:06,799
<i>but its presence is very vague,</i>

157
00:18:06,878 --> 00:18:08,958
<i>so the living do not notice it.</i>

158
00:18:12,801 --> 00:18:14,931
<i>But it can sometimes be seen</i>

159
00:18:15,011 --> 00:18:17,761
<i>when the weather is bad
or if the person has a good sixth sense.</i>

160
00:18:18,181 --> 00:18:19,681
I didn't know there was a hotel here.

161
00:18:19,766 --> 00:18:20,726
You're right.

162
00:18:20,809 --> 00:18:22,979
But it looks kind of scary. Let's just go.

163
00:18:26,731 --> 00:18:30,861
<i>But three to four times a year,
there are people who come in to check.</i>

164
00:18:41,496 --> 00:18:42,496
My goodness.

165
00:18:42,956 --> 00:18:44,826
Our rooms are very expensive.

166
00:18:46,501 --> 00:18:48,631
<i>What do you do with the people
who insist on coming in?</i>

167
00:18:48,711 --> 00:18:50,341
I will check in.

168
00:18:51,714 --> 00:18:54,384
<i>We have a special room
we use for people like them.</i>

169
00:18:57,011 --> 00:18:58,101
Please go inside.

170
00:18:58,596 --> 00:18:59,426
Sure.

171
00:19:28,209 --> 00:19:30,749
A number of people
have checked into this room,

172
00:19:31,087 --> 00:19:33,297
but no one has ever checked out.

173
00:19:37,969 --> 00:19:39,099
What did you do to them?

174
00:19:40,638 --> 00:19:41,678
Do you want to know?

175
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:45,560
Do you want to go in?

176
00:20:14,255 --> 00:20:15,795
I still have many places to show you.

177
00:20:15,882 --> 00:20:18,092
Okay. Then let's move on to the next one.

178
00:20:42,116 --> 00:20:44,326
Why do you need sunglasses
in the middle of the night?

179
00:21:12,814 --> 00:21:14,324
I don't come out here very often.

180
00:21:14,565 --> 00:21:15,725
The sun is too bright.

181
00:21:15,817 --> 00:21:18,397
It's nighttime in the middle of Seoul.
What is this place?

182
00:21:18,486 --> 00:21:20,486
The inside of the hotel
isn't the real world.

183
00:21:20,780 --> 00:21:22,200
The time and space here

184
00:21:22,407 --> 00:21:24,237
are different from the world you live in.

185
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:28,787
Maps and watches
are absolutely useless here.

186
00:21:53,187 --> 00:21:54,857
So this isn't the real world as well?

187
00:21:55,398 --> 00:21:56,318
No.

188
00:21:57,233 --> 00:22:00,453
Nothing in this hotel
exists in the real world.

189
00:22:01,529 --> 00:22:04,369
No matter how pretty it is,
it's not in the real world.

190
00:22:06,576 --> 00:22:07,616
You don't exist

191
00:22:08,411 --> 00:22:09,411
in the real world too?

192
00:22:16,419 --> 00:22:17,459
No,

193
00:22:19,380 --> 00:22:20,380
I don't.

194
00:22:39,776 --> 00:22:42,736
Then I wouldn't die if I fell from here?

195
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:46,280
Be careful. You're still alive.

196
00:22:46,491 --> 00:22:49,991
If a living human falls down, he'll die
because the human body is too weak.

197
00:23:06,844 --> 00:23:09,354
This was what it was like
to have a warm body

198
00:23:10,973 --> 00:23:12,183
with a beating heart.

199
00:23:20,233 --> 00:23:22,693
You need to be alive.
You have many things to do for me.

200
00:23:24,779 --> 00:23:27,069
Stay by my side from now on,
Koo Chan-sung.

201
00:23:29,117 --> 00:23:30,237
If I say no,

202
00:23:31,494 --> 00:23:32,914
are you going to push me over?

203
00:23:49,220 --> 00:23:50,970
It may be a surreal place,

204
00:23:51,305 --> 00:23:53,015
but I demand realistic benefits.

205
00:23:54,308 --> 00:23:57,058
And I am going to wear
whatever shoes I like.

206
00:24:04,026 --> 00:24:05,606
You thought I might push you over?

207
00:24:05,695 --> 00:24:07,065
Is that why you have changed your mind?

208
00:24:07,155 --> 00:24:08,525
I've come this far.

209
00:24:08,614 --> 00:24:11,124
What's the use of running away now?

210
00:24:14,537 --> 00:24:16,157
To be honest, I got curious.

211
00:24:17,206 --> 00:24:18,746
And it looks kind of fun too.

212
00:24:21,210 --> 00:24:22,460
I want to know more

213
00:24:23,546 --> 00:24:26,416
about you and this hotel.

214
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:42,520
Good.

215
00:24:46,110 --> 00:24:48,360
I was going to let it slide
even if you tried to run away

216
00:24:48,446 --> 00:24:49,656
a few more times.

217
00:24:52,033 --> 00:24:54,453
Like I told you before,
you are my cup of tea.

218
00:25:19,435 --> 00:25:20,435
<i>It was her.</i>

219
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:23,520
That woman.

220
00:25:33,074 --> 00:25:34,624
May I get a refill on my coffee?

221
00:25:36,661 --> 00:25:37,701
Yes.

222
00:26:01,310 --> 00:26:03,020
<i>-Oh, right. Honey.
-Yes?</i>

223
00:26:03,104 --> 00:26:05,364
<i>Let's stop by the grocery store
on the way.</i>

224
00:26:05,439 --> 00:26:07,399
We'd have to take a detour.

225
00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:08,776
Let's just go next time.

226
00:26:16,826 --> 00:26:18,036
What happened?

227
00:26:18,661 --> 00:26:20,711
-What should we do?
-Hello?

228
00:26:20,788 --> 00:26:22,788
-What do we do? Is she dead?
-Is this 911?

229
00:26:22,873 --> 00:26:24,753
Someone got hit by a car.

230
00:26:25,376 --> 00:26:26,876
No, it wasn't me.

231
00:26:26,961 --> 00:26:28,751
She suddenly fell from an overpass.

232
00:26:29,213 --> 00:26:31,343
Yes, can you please come quickly?

233
00:26:32,091 --> 00:26:34,721
Oh, right. The location?

234
00:26:36,012 --> 00:26:38,182
We're currently at...

235
00:27:02,747 --> 00:27:03,867
911 EMERGENCY SERVICE

236
00:27:14,842 --> 00:27:16,682
That darn loser.

237
00:27:19,388 --> 00:27:20,508
This is driving me crazy.

238
00:27:22,141 --> 00:27:23,141
Whatever!

239
00:28:13,234 --> 00:28:14,944
What's going on?

240
00:28:17,947 --> 00:28:19,527
What happened to me?

241
00:28:27,248 --> 00:28:28,288
Who are you?

242
00:28:30,918 --> 00:28:32,338
This is mine.

243
00:28:52,773 --> 00:28:55,863
We have a new human hotel manager.

244
00:28:55,943 --> 00:28:58,783
I brought him from one of the best hotels
named by <i>Forbes</i>.

245
00:28:58,863 --> 00:29:00,073
So he'll do a good job.

246
00:29:00,156 --> 00:29:02,526
I know he graduated from Harvard,

247
00:29:02,616 --> 00:29:04,986
but the work we do here
isn't based on knowledge.

248
00:29:05,077 --> 00:29:06,617
He needs to have some guts.

249
00:29:06,704 --> 00:29:08,664
But he seems very weak-hearted,
and that worries me.

250
00:29:08,789 --> 00:29:10,749
How about we leave the position
vacant for a while

251
00:29:10,833 --> 00:29:14,633
and hire someone from the two candidates
you had in mind?

252
00:29:15,504 --> 00:29:17,844
There were two other candidates?

253
00:29:17,923 --> 00:29:19,093
Of course.

254
00:29:19,175 --> 00:29:22,215
The top candidate even knows
how to perform an exorcism, right?

255
00:29:22,762 --> 00:29:23,762
What's the point?

256
00:29:24,388 --> 00:29:26,308
He left to catch some useless ghost.

257
00:29:28,184 --> 00:29:30,984
I ask you in the name of the Father,
the Son, and the Holy Spirit.

258
00:29:31,228 --> 00:29:33,648
Why are you here? What is your name?

259
00:29:44,742 --> 00:29:46,992
-That's enough!
-Do not interfere!

260
00:29:49,371 --> 00:29:53,041
I can't go there
before I catch this ghost.

261
00:29:54,001 --> 00:29:55,211
You should leave.

262
00:29:59,340 --> 00:30:02,340
I ask you in the name of the Father,
the Son, and the Holy Spirit.

263
00:30:02,468 --> 00:30:03,928
What is your name?

264
00:30:04,553 --> 00:30:05,933
Answer me!

265
00:30:06,305 --> 00:30:08,845
-I'm more scared of him.
-Tell me your name!

266
00:30:10,392 --> 00:30:13,562
I gave him the ability to see ghosts
only to see him leave to catch some ghost.

267
00:30:13,646 --> 00:30:15,146
Won't he come back once he catches it?

268
00:30:15,231 --> 00:30:17,481
That'll be impossible.
The ghost is really strong.

269
00:30:18,025 --> 00:30:19,235
Park Il-do, that punk.

270
00:30:21,737 --> 00:30:23,157
Who was the second candidate?

271
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:24,820
He was a fighter pilot.

272
00:30:24,907 --> 00:30:27,617
She went all the way to the States
to find him.

273
00:30:27,785 --> 00:30:29,695
But he eventually left in that thing.

274
00:30:29,995 --> 00:30:31,155
In what thing?

275
00:31:50,993 --> 00:31:52,833
<i>I don't need the top two candidates.</i>

276
00:31:52,953 --> 00:31:54,503
Koo Chan-sung is here, so we're good.

277
00:31:54,622 --> 00:31:56,042
His office is ready.

278
00:31:56,123 --> 00:31:59,673
Mr. No knew he was going to leave
and had the office cleaned up beforehand.

279
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:03,550
He worked here for 30 years,
but he didn't leave a single trace behind.

280
00:32:03,631 --> 00:32:04,671
Yes, he did.

281
00:32:05,674 --> 00:32:06,724
That over there.

282
00:32:07,343 --> 00:32:08,933
Mr. No took that photo.

283
00:32:11,347 --> 00:32:13,887
So many humans worked here,

284
00:32:13,974 --> 00:32:15,604
but they're all so vague to me.

285
00:32:16,143 --> 00:32:19,153
How many people were here
including Mr. No?

286
00:32:19,647 --> 00:32:21,317
Ms. Jang is the only one who knows that.

287
00:32:21,857 --> 00:32:24,607
There's been no one special.
What's the point of counting?

288
00:32:27,029 --> 00:32:29,369
What are you doing? Get back to work.

289
00:33:17,246 --> 00:33:19,826
He was nothing more
than the 48th human to work here.

290
00:33:21,125 --> 00:33:22,455
And Koo Chan-sung

291
00:33:24,044 --> 00:33:26,214
will just be the 49th human to work here.
Nothing more.

292
00:33:44,356 --> 00:33:47,936
MANAGER KOO CHAN-SUNG

293
00:33:54,575 --> 00:33:56,905
I caved in way too easily.
That was so not like me.

294
00:33:59,121 --> 00:34:00,331
Why did I do that?

295
00:34:07,963 --> 00:34:10,593
This was what it was like
to have a warm body

296
00:34:13,093 --> 00:34:14,263
with a beating heart.

297
00:34:16,972 --> 00:34:18,472
I got too carried away.

298
00:34:29,777 --> 00:34:33,237
Ms. Jang told us to say hello
to the new manager.

299
00:34:34,239 --> 00:34:35,909
If you all work here,

300
00:34:36,575 --> 00:34:39,535
that means you're all ghosts, right?

301
00:34:39,828 --> 00:34:41,658
I died about 500 years ago.

302
00:34:42,956 --> 00:34:44,626
She died 200 years ago.

303
00:34:46,001 --> 00:34:48,251
And he died 70 years ago.
He's the youngest among us.

304
00:34:55,969 --> 00:34:59,099
I was a scholar who studied very hard
when I was alive.

305
00:34:59,932 --> 00:35:01,482
After a long period of studying,

306
00:35:01,558 --> 00:35:03,728
I passed the National State Exam
with the highest score.

307
00:35:06,814 --> 00:35:09,824
<i>But I suddenly died
right before achieving my lifelong dream.</i>

308
00:35:11,151 --> 00:35:14,241
<i>And while I was wandering around,
I found Man-wol Inn.</i>

309
00:35:22,788 --> 00:35:24,958
I've been here the longest.

310
00:35:25,791 --> 00:35:28,291
You said you used to study.
Then what do you do here?

311
00:35:28,377 --> 00:35:30,997
I used to be very bright
when it came to writing poems.

312
00:35:31,088 --> 00:35:32,548
And now,

313
00:35:32,631 --> 00:35:33,971
I'm a bartender.

314
00:35:39,638 --> 00:35:43,018
So you're the bartender
who's in charge of the food and beverages.

315
00:35:43,142 --> 00:35:46,602
I was the eldest daughter-in-law
of a prestigious family.

316
00:35:47,938 --> 00:35:52,148
<i>But I ended up getting murdered
by my own family.</i>

317
00:36:14,006 --> 00:36:15,666
While staying here,

318
00:36:16,175 --> 00:36:19,925
I'll make sure I see the last member
of that loathful family die

319
00:36:20,637 --> 00:36:23,217
with my own eyes
before I leave for the afterlife.

320
00:36:24,933 --> 00:36:27,023
You must have a deep grudge.

321
00:36:28,228 --> 00:36:30,188
I'm in charge of the rooms.

322
00:36:30,898 --> 00:36:32,228
I see, ma'am.

323
00:36:32,566 --> 00:36:34,816
I died during the Korean War.

324
00:37:04,806 --> 00:37:06,636
<i>This was called Man-wol Hostel
at that time.</i>

325
00:37:06,934 --> 00:37:09,104
<i>It wasn't doing so well back then.</i>

326
00:37:09,686 --> 00:37:13,516
I'm waiting to go with my sister
who's still alive.

327
00:37:14,399 --> 00:37:17,239
All of us have long stories to tell.

328
00:37:17,736 --> 00:37:19,106
As for me--

329
00:37:19,196 --> 00:37:22,196
We all came here
as guests at first. But now

330
00:37:22,282 --> 00:37:24,412
we're working here, extending our stays.

331
00:37:24,868 --> 00:37:27,288
Aside from Ms. Jang,
the three of us have been here

332
00:37:27,371 --> 00:37:28,831
the longest.

333
00:37:29,206 --> 00:37:32,166
Then did Ms. Jang come here
as a guest like you,

334
00:37:32,251 --> 00:37:33,961
and ended up staying for a long term?

335
00:37:34,044 --> 00:37:35,054
No.

336
00:37:35,128 --> 00:37:37,378
Ms. Jang is the owner of Hotel del Luna.

337
00:37:37,464 --> 00:37:38,764
Owner of what?

338
00:37:38,924 --> 00:37:41,474
She's just tied down here
for a punishment from that crone.

339
00:37:41,843 --> 00:37:42,803
She's being tied down?

340
00:37:42,886 --> 00:37:45,926
There's a huge tree in our garden, but--

341
00:37:48,433 --> 00:37:49,813
Do we have a garden?

342
00:37:49,893 --> 00:37:52,273
I think we left the front desk and the bar
unattended for too long.

343
00:37:52,354 --> 00:37:54,234
We better go.

344
00:37:55,274 --> 00:37:57,784
I can't be lazy at work,
or I'll be sent to the other world.

345
00:37:57,859 --> 00:38:01,909
I'll tell you my long story at the bar
while treating you to a martini.

346
00:38:11,915 --> 00:38:14,955
I think you're done for the day.
You can go home now.

347
00:38:15,419 --> 00:38:17,549
Where is the garden with the huge tree?

348
00:38:18,088 --> 00:38:19,378
I didn't get to see it today.

349
00:38:19,464 --> 00:38:22,344
She probably didn't show it to you
because it's unnecessary.

350
00:38:24,928 --> 00:38:26,928
Is there some kind of tie between Ms. Jang

351
00:38:27,014 --> 00:38:28,434
and that tree?

352
00:38:32,436 --> 00:38:33,646
Mr. Koo.

353
00:38:34,479 --> 00:38:37,399
How long do you want to work here?

354
00:38:39,776 --> 00:38:42,396
As short as possible
since I didn't come here out of choice.

355
00:38:42,487 --> 00:38:45,617
Then, it'd be best to keep
your curiosity to a minimum.

356
00:38:48,118 --> 00:38:52,038
You must mean the more I know,
the longer I'll be tied to this place.

357
00:38:52,164 --> 00:38:55,004
The rest of us will take care
of hosting the guests.

358
00:38:55,083 --> 00:38:58,343
All you have to do is do the work

359
00:38:58,420 --> 00:39:00,090
related to the humans.

360
00:39:02,632 --> 00:39:03,512
I'll do that.

361
00:40:19,751 --> 00:40:22,171
Hey, are you going to work already?

362
00:40:23,380 --> 00:40:25,300
No, I just got off work.

363
00:40:25,382 --> 00:40:26,472
Did you have a night shift?

364
00:40:27,050 --> 00:40:27,880
No.

365
00:40:28,301 --> 00:40:30,101
I have to quit the hotel I'm working at.

366
00:40:31,012 --> 00:40:33,102
-Why?
-I'm going to work at a different one.

367
00:40:33,181 --> 00:40:34,221
Which hotel?

368
00:40:34,307 --> 00:40:36,477
Why quit the best hotel in Seoul?

369
00:40:36,560 --> 00:40:38,310
The hotel I'll work at

370
00:40:38,478 --> 00:40:41,818
has a private beach
and a soaring rooftop bar.

371
00:40:42,065 --> 00:40:44,185
Is there such a hotel in Seoul?

372
00:40:45,193 --> 00:40:46,193
I want to go there too.

373
00:40:47,362 --> 00:40:48,242
You can't.

374
00:40:49,406 --> 00:40:51,366
If you come, you'll be in Room 404.

375
00:40:54,077 --> 00:40:55,697
What's in Room 404?

376
00:40:56,580 --> 00:40:57,790
Is it a suite?

377
00:41:00,459 --> 00:41:01,629
I'm so tired.

378
00:41:04,463 --> 00:41:07,223
Hurray!

379
00:41:15,265 --> 00:41:16,095
Yes.

380
00:41:16,641 --> 00:41:18,061
This is the real world.

381
00:41:18,393 --> 00:41:20,403
I have a place to stay,
and I have a friend.

382
00:41:20,520 --> 00:41:22,440
I have lots of other hotels
asking me to come.

383
00:41:23,190 --> 00:41:24,270
Don't get confused.

384
00:41:29,613 --> 00:41:30,823
I'm finally calming down.

385
00:41:32,157 --> 00:41:33,327
This really helps.

386
00:41:58,475 --> 00:42:00,595
Something strange followed me
to the real world.

387
00:43:00,537 --> 00:43:01,577
It's a moon.

388
00:43:02,956 --> 00:43:04,246
It's to show that it's mine.

389
00:43:26,646 --> 00:43:27,646
Man...

390
00:43:31,026 --> 00:43:32,066
Wol.

391
00:43:33,612 --> 00:43:34,822
This is how you write it.

392
00:43:35,071 --> 00:43:38,411
MAN-WOL

393
00:43:44,664 --> 00:43:46,754
I'm paying you back
for giving me good wine.

394
00:44:54,776 --> 00:44:56,396
DEL LUNA

395
00:44:58,696 --> 00:45:01,696
She was in my dream,
and now she's calling me.

396
00:45:02,200 --> 00:45:03,580
It's getting me confused.

397
00:45:06,746 --> 00:45:08,456
What took you so long to pick up?

398
00:45:11,584 --> 00:45:12,544
What is it?

399
00:45:13,920 --> 00:45:16,880
I have your first job for you.

400
00:45:17,132 --> 00:45:18,052
What is it?

401
00:45:19,384 --> 00:45:21,344
I want to sell
the painting of Baekdu Mountain.

402
00:45:24,139 --> 00:45:25,059
What?

403
00:45:32,981 --> 00:45:34,901
The soul of the mythical creature

404
00:45:35,483 --> 00:45:38,703
made the aura of this painting
even better.

405
00:45:39,195 --> 00:45:41,315
I'll be able to get
twice its original price.

406
00:45:42,449 --> 00:45:43,449
If we sell this,

407
00:45:45,243 --> 00:45:46,913
what about the tiger inside?

408
00:45:47,495 --> 00:45:49,155
The tiger has just left.

409
00:45:49,831 --> 00:45:51,041
This is an empty painting.

410
00:45:51,374 --> 00:45:52,334
The tiger has left?

411
00:45:53,334 --> 00:45:55,714
The tiger lived in a zoo all his life.

412
00:45:56,296 --> 00:45:58,756
He got sick of living in Baekdu Mountain
in a couple of days.

413
00:45:59,007 --> 00:46:01,087
He went to the afterlife
after playing there for a few days.

414
00:46:01,384 --> 00:46:03,644
I'm sure he'll be reborn in blessing.

415
00:46:03,720 --> 00:46:05,470
Is this why you asked me
to get the painting?

416
00:46:05,597 --> 00:46:06,427
To sell it?

417
00:46:06,514 --> 00:46:08,144
Not because you cared about the tiger.

418
00:46:08,975 --> 00:46:10,805
Of course I care about the tiger.

419
00:46:11,436 --> 00:46:13,476
I even wore this for him.

420
00:46:14,022 --> 00:46:14,982
Hey!

421
00:46:16,065 --> 00:46:17,935
Make sure you get a good price for this.

422
00:46:18,026 --> 00:46:19,316
Then as a reward,

423
00:46:19,611 --> 00:46:22,531
I'll get you a tiger print suit like this.

424
00:46:23,281 --> 00:46:26,161
No, thanks. Who would wear such a thing?

425
00:46:26,326 --> 00:46:28,746
Why not? You love the poop color.

426
00:46:28,828 --> 00:46:32,618
I even got the new car
in that color, just for you.

427
00:46:32,916 --> 00:46:35,336
-A new car?
-Make sure to sell this by today.

428
00:46:35,418 --> 00:46:36,708
I have to pick up the new car.

429
00:46:36,794 --> 00:46:37,884
You bought a car?

430
00:46:37,962 --> 00:46:40,422
The car I drove the other day
was also a new one.

431
00:46:40,507 --> 00:46:43,717
You're right. I'm broke now
because I bought another new car.

432
00:46:44,844 --> 00:46:46,804
Make sure you get a good price
for this painting.

433
00:46:46,971 --> 00:46:48,811
At least twice its original price.

434
00:46:55,980 --> 00:47:00,820
<i>Let's go pick up my new car</i>

435
00:47:03,780 --> 00:47:05,110
I must've been crazy.

436
00:47:05,865 --> 00:47:09,035
What more is there to know?
She's nothing but a money chaser.

437
00:47:13,373 --> 00:47:15,583
Is he really gone? Is he not in there?

438
00:47:22,131 --> 00:47:22,971
Roar.

439
00:47:25,385 --> 00:47:28,755
Roar!

440
00:47:49,826 --> 00:47:51,786
KIM YU-NA

441
00:48:01,921 --> 00:48:05,011
That's not who you are.
You died right here!

442
00:48:14,100 --> 00:48:15,770
Give my body back to me!

443
00:48:20,773 --> 00:48:23,363
Yes, Director. Thank you
for introducing me to him.

444
00:48:24,068 --> 00:48:26,108
Yes, I'm heading to the gallery right now.

445
00:48:26,529 --> 00:48:27,699
I'll see you soon.

446
00:48:31,326 --> 00:48:32,656
Give my body back to me!

447
00:49:39,060 --> 00:49:42,310
Seems like Mr. Third Choice brought in
a very annoying guest.

448
00:49:42,605 --> 00:49:45,565
She must have some issues.
She keeps saying she's not dead.

449
00:49:46,067 --> 00:49:49,067
This isn't our first time
seeing the dead saying they're alive.

450
00:49:49,153 --> 00:49:51,783
They always say that they're alive,
they can't die or ask why they died.

451
00:49:51,864 --> 00:49:53,374
We hear that all the time.

452
00:49:53,449 --> 00:49:55,369
Ms. Jang will handle it, right?

453
00:50:01,416 --> 00:50:02,826
I told you to go sell a painting.

454
00:50:02,917 --> 00:50:05,087
Why did you bring in an unwanted guest?

455
00:50:05,211 --> 00:50:06,301
Are you a tout or what?

456
00:50:06,754 --> 00:50:07,764
What did you say?

457
00:50:08,798 --> 00:50:11,338
You said that you comfort souls here.

458
00:50:12,301 --> 00:50:15,511
She seems like she has issues.
Why don't you come up with a solution?

459
00:50:15,847 --> 00:50:18,217
You said you saw her other self
wandering around?

460
00:50:18,307 --> 00:50:21,057
She said she was robbed of her body.
If it's true, we should get it back.

461
00:50:21,144 --> 00:50:24,694
What you've brought is a soul
that came out of her living body.

462
00:50:27,859 --> 00:50:30,819
So you're saying
that her body is out there without a soul?

463
00:50:30,903 --> 00:50:32,493
You said she was robbed of her body.

464
00:50:32,572 --> 00:50:34,662
Her body must be taken over
by another ghost.

465
00:50:40,121 --> 00:50:42,791
What's wrong with Yu-na?

466
00:50:43,291 --> 00:50:45,631
Yu-na bullied her the most.

467
00:50:45,710 --> 00:50:47,800
Maybe she feels guilty
for everything she did to her.

468
00:50:48,254 --> 00:50:49,884
She's acting like she actually feels bad.

469
00:50:57,180 --> 00:50:58,350
Is this the girl's house?

470
00:50:58,931 --> 00:51:02,311
Yes, Yu-na is the only child
of this household.

471
00:51:03,853 --> 00:51:06,813
Their one and only daughter's body is
taken over by a ghost.

472
00:51:06,898 --> 00:51:08,188
Of course we should get it back.

473
00:51:08,274 --> 00:51:11,244
I think I already know the answer,

474
00:51:11,319 --> 00:51:12,949
but are you going to force them pay you?

475
00:51:14,280 --> 00:51:16,240
This isn't just a rich house.

476
00:51:16,949 --> 00:51:19,119
That's the poop colored car
that I'm in love with.

477
00:51:19,202 --> 00:51:23,042
It's very difficult to buy that car now,
but they already bought it before I did.

478
00:51:23,998 --> 00:51:26,538
That means that they're filthy rich.

479
00:51:29,962 --> 00:51:33,262
We need to find out
why this is happening, right?

480
00:51:33,341 --> 00:51:34,471
It's because of a necklace.

481
00:51:34,550 --> 00:51:36,680
It belongs to the dead friend
who took her body.

482
00:51:36,761 --> 00:51:39,391
The ghost's deep grudge followed her,
stuck to the necklace.

483
00:51:39,472 --> 00:51:40,772
Then it took over her body.

484
00:51:40,848 --> 00:51:42,598
I thought they were friends.
Why would she do that?

485
00:51:42,767 --> 00:51:46,017
Stop asking questions.
You said we need to get the body back.

486
00:51:46,354 --> 00:51:48,364
Then that's all we need to do.

487
00:51:55,988 --> 00:51:57,028
Go after her.

488
00:51:58,658 --> 00:51:59,578
Hey!

489
00:52:12,046 --> 00:52:13,046
Let me go!

490
00:52:15,216 --> 00:52:16,756
I'm going to kill her body.

491
00:52:16,926 --> 00:52:19,756
This isn't even your body.
Why are you doing this to a friend?

492
00:52:20,680 --> 00:52:22,270
She's not a friend.

493
00:52:24,183 --> 00:52:25,773
She's the one who killed me.

494
00:52:32,650 --> 00:52:34,440
JEONG SU-JEONG

495
00:52:37,989 --> 00:52:39,029
Give it back to me.

496
00:52:39,323 --> 00:52:40,833
You live on social assistance,

497
00:52:40,908 --> 00:52:43,118
and you waste your money
on something like this?

498
00:52:43,953 --> 00:52:45,793
Do you have no conscience?

499
00:52:46,372 --> 00:52:48,212
The money you get is for your meals.

500
00:52:49,959 --> 00:52:52,879
This is what we call a waste of tax money.

501
00:52:54,630 --> 00:52:55,630
Give it back.

502
00:52:56,799 --> 00:52:58,379
Give it back!

503
00:52:58,467 --> 00:53:00,467
Take it if you can.

504
00:53:00,928 --> 00:53:03,388
-Here you go.
-Give it back to me!

505
00:53:04,724 --> 00:53:05,734
Give it back!

506
00:53:06,809 --> 00:53:07,849
Give it to me.

507
00:53:15,109 --> 00:53:16,109
You little!

508
00:53:17,028 --> 00:53:18,278
Let go of me!

509
00:53:33,210 --> 00:53:35,380
I can't remember anything
after falling off the bridge.

510
00:53:35,922 --> 00:53:37,632
When I came to consciousness,

511
00:53:38,883 --> 00:53:40,553
I realized that I'm in her body...

512
00:53:42,553 --> 00:53:44,683
with my necklace in her hand.

513
00:53:50,645 --> 00:53:52,605
Are you here to give Yu-na her body back?

514
00:53:52,688 --> 00:53:54,108
She killed me!

515
00:54:01,405 --> 00:54:02,525
That's it.

516
00:54:03,115 --> 00:54:05,075
Get me my body back with that now.

517
00:54:05,159 --> 00:54:06,829
The grudge in here...

518
00:54:08,871 --> 00:54:10,921
doesn't disappear that easily.

519
00:54:10,998 --> 00:54:12,578
Just tell my parents.

520
00:54:13,084 --> 00:54:15,344
They'll do anything for me.

521
00:54:17,129 --> 00:54:18,299
Of course they should.

522
00:54:19,840 --> 00:54:21,680
They're the ones who made you after all.

523
00:54:30,893 --> 00:54:34,273
What is it that you wanted
to talk about our daughter?

524
00:54:36,190 --> 00:54:39,280
Yu-na murdered someone.

525
00:54:43,406 --> 00:54:44,776
Did you know

526
00:54:44,865 --> 00:54:47,735
that one of Yu-na's classmates
committed suicide on an overpass?

527
00:54:49,537 --> 00:54:51,117
That's not entirely true.

528
00:54:52,039 --> 00:54:53,749
Your daughter killed her.

529
00:54:57,253 --> 00:55:00,423
This necklace is the evidence.

530
00:55:07,346 --> 00:55:09,636
What is it that you want?

531
00:55:13,144 --> 00:55:15,154
I came to collect the price.

532
00:55:18,107 --> 00:55:21,857
Do you think it's wrong of me
to kill Yu-na?

533
00:55:22,194 --> 00:55:23,574
Let's find another way.

534
00:55:24,780 --> 00:55:26,030
What way?

535
00:55:29,452 --> 00:55:31,792
No matter what I do,
I can't come back to life.

536
00:55:34,582 --> 00:55:36,422
I wanted to live!

537
00:55:38,669 --> 00:55:40,549
Even when they called me a parasite,

538
00:55:41,630 --> 00:55:43,800
I still wanted to live on.

539
00:55:50,765 --> 00:55:51,885
Let go of me!

540
00:55:53,476 --> 00:55:54,726
Please let go of me.

541
00:55:58,773 --> 00:56:00,613
I can't let her return to this body

542
00:56:02,193 --> 00:56:04,073
and live like nothing happened.

543
00:56:07,406 --> 00:56:08,656
Please let go of me.

544
00:56:20,586 --> 00:56:21,666
Wait, just a second.

545
00:56:22,088 --> 00:56:23,628
I'll go get the necklace.

546
00:56:25,424 --> 00:56:27,764
You should just live in this body, okay?

547
00:56:37,686 --> 00:56:38,766
Where is the necklace?

548
00:56:41,565 --> 00:56:43,645
We can't let her return to her body yet!

549
00:56:44,026 --> 00:56:45,566
It'd be too unfair for that girl!

550
00:56:45,903 --> 00:56:47,323
I already returned the necklace.

551
00:56:48,572 --> 00:56:49,872
It's in the hands of her parents.

552
00:57:23,816 --> 00:57:26,736
So this necklace belonged
to that dead girl, right?

553
00:57:27,653 --> 00:57:29,663
That woman told us
this is the only evidence.

554
00:57:31,907 --> 00:57:34,697
There are two ways
to pay for what she did.

555
00:57:34,910 --> 00:57:36,700
One, take this necklace as evidence

556
00:57:36,787 --> 00:57:39,417
to prove your daughter's wrongdoing
and punish her.

557
00:57:39,540 --> 00:57:41,960
She should also apologize
to the dead girl's soul.

558
00:57:42,084 --> 00:57:43,254
Two,

559
00:57:44,253 --> 00:57:48,053
you buy my silence
and get rid of this necklace.

560
00:58:04,315 --> 00:58:06,065
I'll pay as much as you want.

561
00:58:07,234 --> 00:58:08,154
Please...

562
00:58:09,987 --> 00:58:11,657
give it to us and keep it a secret.

563
00:58:13,657 --> 00:58:14,907
So you made your decision.

564
00:58:16,869 --> 00:58:21,169
You'll have to pay a big price.

565
00:58:30,758 --> 00:58:33,508
Everything will go back to normal, right?

566
00:58:33,719 --> 00:58:34,719
Of course.

567
00:58:35,596 --> 00:58:37,386
Once that necklace is gone,

568
00:58:38,098 --> 00:58:40,478
no one will know that you killed her.

569
00:58:41,101 --> 00:58:42,561
No one will know, right?

570
00:58:44,021 --> 00:58:46,111
I told you
that her grudge is very deep, didn't I?

571
00:58:47,149 --> 00:58:48,649
Once that necklace is burned,

572
00:58:49,318 --> 00:58:52,988
your chance to be forgiven for
what you did will be gone for good too.

573
00:58:54,740 --> 00:58:55,820
It doesn't matter.

574
00:58:58,202 --> 00:58:59,122
It does.

575
00:59:00,037 --> 00:59:01,747
You won't ever be able to go back.

576
00:59:02,456 --> 00:59:03,286
Pardon?

577
00:59:04,250 --> 00:59:07,210
I'm saying that your soul

578
00:59:08,379 --> 00:59:11,259
will really die without anyone realizing.

579
00:59:15,928 --> 00:59:16,888
Darn it.

580
00:59:27,565 --> 00:59:29,355
What's done is done, she's already dead.

581
00:59:29,483 --> 00:59:31,743
Our Yu-na should continue
to have a good life.

582
00:59:32,861 --> 00:59:33,951
Yes, she should.

583
00:59:34,363 --> 00:59:36,413
None of this happened.

584
00:59:37,283 --> 00:59:38,533
But what do you think...

585
00:59:40,452 --> 00:59:42,712
that woman meant by the last comment?

586
00:59:44,957 --> 00:59:45,827
Right.

587
00:59:46,375 --> 00:59:51,415
You should know that the choice you made
will kill your daughter's soul.

588
00:59:57,553 --> 00:59:58,603
No!

589
01:00:01,765 --> 01:00:04,055
No! What do I do?

590
01:00:05,853 --> 01:00:09,403
Mom, take it out! Mom! Please!

591
01:00:09,481 --> 01:00:11,781
Please take it out, Mom!

592
01:00:11,984 --> 01:00:14,864
I said, take it out! Take it out!

593
01:00:39,845 --> 01:00:41,465
<i>You should live in that body now.</i>

594
01:00:42,014 --> 01:00:44,104
<i>Although you're parasitic on the body,</i>

595
01:00:44,850 --> 01:00:48,100
<i>try your best to survive again.</i>

596
01:00:54,735 --> 01:00:57,525
DEATH

597
01:01:08,540 --> 01:01:11,000
<i>She has become a true parasite.</i>

598
01:01:13,754 --> 01:01:14,844
However,

599
01:01:15,798 --> 01:01:17,418
she found herself a golden host.

600
01:01:19,134 --> 01:01:22,724
I bet they'll spoil her not knowing
she's only their daughter's shell.

601
01:01:22,930 --> 01:01:24,140
That young girl

602
01:01:24,848 --> 01:01:27,098
will be tortured
while watching her own shell.

603
01:01:27,601 --> 01:01:28,771
I feel bad for her.

604
01:01:29,395 --> 01:01:32,145
She's only paying for what she did.

605
01:01:36,193 --> 01:01:38,863
She's just tied down here
for a punishment from that crone.

606
01:01:41,240 --> 01:01:44,370
Are you also paying for what you did?

607
01:01:53,502 --> 01:01:54,922
I heard you're being punished.

608
01:01:57,715 --> 01:01:58,715
I am.

609
01:02:00,300 --> 01:02:02,930
Someone told me
that I'm arrogant and foolish.

610
01:02:04,304 --> 01:02:05,604
Although I don't agree with it.

611
01:02:09,476 --> 01:02:10,516
Right.

612
01:02:11,353 --> 01:02:14,233
What was that? Did you just say, "Right"?

613
01:02:14,857 --> 01:02:16,067
Are you mocking me?

614
01:02:16,525 --> 01:02:17,475
No, I'm not.

615
01:02:18,402 --> 01:02:20,862
Sometimes. No, very rarely,

616
01:02:22,281 --> 01:02:23,821
I feel bad for you.

617
01:02:38,422 --> 01:02:40,172
TEXT MESSAGE

618
01:02:40,382 --> 01:02:41,382
What is this?

619
01:02:41,967 --> 01:02:44,217
They cancelled the car I pre-ordered.

620
01:02:46,221 --> 01:02:48,891
What kind of bullshit is this?

621
01:02:50,100 --> 01:02:52,600
How is this possible?
Are they looking down on me?

622
01:02:53,187 --> 01:02:54,347
They're dead meat.

623
01:02:54,855 --> 01:02:56,185
Do you take me for a fool?

624
01:02:56,607 --> 01:02:57,897
Forget it.

625
01:02:58,859 --> 01:03:00,149
Give me the one in charge.

626
01:03:00,569 --> 01:03:02,239
I said, the one in charge!

627
01:03:07,075 --> 01:03:10,495
When Ms. Jang gets angry,
she drinks champagne in bulk.

628
01:03:10,620 --> 01:03:12,500
Mr. No always prepared it for her.

629
01:03:13,748 --> 01:03:17,668
I didn't know I'd be required
to serve Ms. Jang alcohol.

630
01:03:17,877 --> 01:03:19,707
You're so unlucky.

631
01:03:19,963 --> 01:03:21,843
You were the third choice,

632
01:03:22,257 --> 01:03:25,007
so we didn't expect
you'd end up as our manager.

633
01:03:25,260 --> 01:03:26,510
I was the third choice?

634
01:03:32,684 --> 01:03:34,894
They told me not to tell you about that.

635
01:03:36,646 --> 01:03:40,606
Are you saying I was the third choice
for the job?

636
01:03:40,734 --> 01:03:41,904
-No.
-This means

637
01:03:42,110 --> 01:03:44,820
there were two other candidates before me.

638
01:03:44,946 --> 01:03:46,946
You're here now, so you're the winner.

639
01:03:47,032 --> 01:03:48,872
It's a feat that I'm not happy about.

640
01:03:50,577 --> 01:03:51,827
Here it is.

641
01:03:57,459 --> 01:03:58,419
What is this?

642
01:03:58,501 --> 01:04:00,301
This sign shows
that it belongs to Ms. Jang.

643
01:04:00,378 --> 01:04:02,128
Anything with this means it's Ms. Jang's.

644
01:04:04,299 --> 01:04:05,299
<i>It's a moon.</i>

645
01:04:06,217 --> 01:04:07,677
<i>It's to show that it's mine.</i>

646
01:04:13,683 --> 01:04:14,683
Come this way.

647
01:04:33,703 --> 01:04:34,703
Ms. Choe.

648
01:04:36,206 --> 01:04:39,626
Do you know what Ms. Jang was like
when she was alive?

649
01:04:40,335 --> 01:04:43,205
What does it mean
that she's tied down for a punishment?

650
01:04:43,296 --> 01:04:45,966
You're just a passer-by here.

651
01:04:47,258 --> 01:04:49,798
Like these people who stopped by
over the many years,

652
01:04:50,220 --> 01:04:52,310
just consider you're only visiting
for a moment,

653
01:04:52,680 --> 01:04:55,390
and leave this place as soon as possible
as you wish.

654
01:05:33,138 --> 01:05:36,598
MAN-WOL HOSTEL

655
01:05:41,521 --> 01:05:45,361
Why are you enduring like that
for such a long time?

656
01:05:58,788 --> 01:06:00,038
MAN-WOL INN

657
01:06:07,297 --> 01:06:08,337
Is this that tree?

658
01:06:41,498 --> 01:06:43,038
There are no leaves.

659
01:06:47,504 --> 01:06:48,674
What are you doing here?

660
01:06:56,137 --> 01:06:58,597
You didn't show me the garden,
so I came by myself.

661
01:06:59,224 --> 01:07:01,814
Guests cannot come here.
So you don't need to see this.

662
01:07:03,770 --> 01:07:05,190
Is this that tree?

663
01:07:05,271 --> 01:07:07,231
The tree that my father touched.

664
01:07:08,483 --> 01:07:09,983
The reason why I was sold here.

665
01:07:10,068 --> 01:07:11,068
You're right.

666
01:07:11,236 --> 01:07:13,316
You're paying the price too.

667
01:07:16,699 --> 01:07:18,159
But it didn't have to be me.

668
01:07:18,243 --> 01:07:19,793
I heard I was the third one on the list.

669
01:07:21,955 --> 01:07:23,915
I really thought it had to be me.

670
01:07:23,998 --> 01:07:26,708
You said I am your cup of tea,
so I made a huge decision to come here.

671
01:07:27,043 --> 01:07:28,503
But I wasn't your first or second choice.

672
01:07:31,172 --> 01:07:34,552
Yes, there were first and second
candidates before you.

673
01:07:36,219 --> 01:07:37,679
Was I really the third choice?

674
01:07:37,762 --> 01:07:39,682
Wasn't I the fourth,
or the fifth one by any chance?

675
01:07:40,098 --> 01:07:41,768
Who said you were the third choice?

676
01:07:42,559 --> 01:07:44,519
-There were more before me?
-You're

677
01:07:45,270 --> 01:07:46,270
the zeroth choice.

678
01:07:47,939 --> 01:07:49,269
The zeroth choice.

679
01:07:49,816 --> 01:07:53,066
You're right. It has to be you
because you are my cup of tea.

680
01:07:56,906 --> 01:07:58,156
Do you want some champagne?

681
01:07:59,450 --> 01:08:02,830
You said you'll sell the Baekdu Mountain
painting for a good price. So have some.

682
01:08:04,038 --> 01:08:07,208
Do you think the tiger saw
what he wanted to see in the painting?

683
01:08:08,251 --> 01:08:10,341
He probably left without complaining
because he did.

684
01:08:11,337 --> 01:08:15,047
He saw the past like a dream,
a time where he could never go back.

685
01:08:15,925 --> 01:08:17,335
He got pretty lucky.

686
01:08:21,931 --> 01:08:24,181
I'm sure you too have
things you miss in the past

687
01:08:24,517 --> 01:08:25,977
that you can never go back to.

688
01:08:34,027 --> 01:08:35,447
I think I saw that.

689
01:08:38,531 --> 01:08:40,201
I told you that I saw you in a dream.

690
01:08:40,908 --> 01:08:41,868
In a dream?

691
01:08:43,036 --> 01:08:44,286
You were smiling

692
01:08:44,746 --> 01:08:46,036
under a huge tree.

693
01:08:47,332 --> 01:08:50,922
When someone said he'd build you a house,
you said mean things just as you do now,

694
01:08:51,252 --> 01:08:52,502
but you were happy.

695
01:08:56,382 --> 01:08:58,722
The moon shined above the wilderness
where you were drinking,

696
01:08:59,552 --> 01:09:01,262
and it was filled
with sounds of instruments,

697
01:09:01,512 --> 01:09:03,062
along with your laughter.

698
01:09:10,647 --> 01:09:12,567
You were full of joy and happiness.

699
01:09:13,566 --> 01:09:16,526
You weren't alone like you are now.
You had someone by your side.

700
01:09:18,529 --> 01:09:21,029
<i>The man who taught you
how to write your name, Man-wol.</i>

701
01:09:22,408 --> 01:09:24,448
<i>Is he the person you miss the most</i>

702
01:09:25,495 --> 01:09:26,695
<i>in your past?</i>

703
01:09:39,300 --> 01:09:40,340
You...

704
01:09:43,179 --> 01:09:44,639
You really...

705
01:09:47,100 --> 01:09:48,100
saw him.

706
01:09:50,937 --> 01:09:51,937
You have been

707
01:09:52,397 --> 01:09:54,147
waiting for that person

708
01:09:55,274 --> 01:09:57,074
over this long period of time.

709
01:11:35,291 --> 01:11:36,831
How do you see...

710
01:11:39,378 --> 01:11:40,418
such things?

711
01:11:41,380 --> 01:11:42,420
I don't know.

712
01:11:43,549 --> 01:11:45,179
Why do I see you?

713
01:11:45,802 --> 01:11:47,972
I'm scared
that I may have to pay the price for it.

714
01:11:50,765 --> 01:11:52,055
Jang Man-wol.

715
01:11:56,729 --> 01:11:58,769
Since I began to see you,

716
01:12:00,274 --> 01:12:01,614
I've been thinking of you...

717
01:12:03,236 --> 01:12:04,856
very much, awfully a lot.

718
01:12:10,493 --> 01:12:11,833
Jang Man-wol, I'm saying...

719
01:12:13,621 --> 01:12:14,961
you are devouring...

720
01:12:16,457 --> 01:12:18,077
all my nights and dreams.

721
01:13:17,435 --> 01:13:19,555
<i>The old memories that shriveled up</i>

722
01:13:19,896 --> 01:13:21,766
<i>crawled out again because of you.</i>

723
01:13:22,773 --> 01:13:24,363
<i>So I need to check this for myself.</i>

724
01:13:24,442 --> 01:13:27,492
Chan-sung. Starting today,
you will deal with ghost guests.

725
01:13:28,696 --> 01:13:30,696
There's someone she really wants to see.

726
01:13:30,781 --> 01:13:32,621
Every single ghost has someone
that they want to see!

727
01:13:32,700 --> 01:13:35,080
You said the owner was a maniac, right?

728
01:13:35,620 --> 01:13:37,830
-Is that so?
<i>-Leaves have sprouted from the dry tree...</i>

729
01:13:37,914 --> 01:13:39,254
<i>I'm trying to take care of you.</i>

730
01:13:40,291 --> 01:13:41,331
I'm sorry.

731
01:13:41,709 --> 01:13:44,709
<i>Chan-sung, come to my hotel if you die.</i>

732
01:13:46,964 --> 01:13:48,974
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu

733
01:13:50,168 --> 01:13:52,418
I'm sure you too have
things you miss in the past

734
01:13:52,879 --> 01:13:54,209
that you can never go back to.

735
01:13:56,883 --> 01:13:58,343
I think I saw that.

736
01:14:01,345 --> 01:14:02,965
I told you that I saw you in a dream.

737
01:14:03,681 --> 01:14:04,521
In a dream?

738
01:14:04,599 --> 01:14:05,769
You were smiling

739
01:14:06,225 --> 01:14:07,435
under a huge tree.

740
01:14:08,644 --> 01:14:10,354
When someone said he'd build you a house,

741
01:14:10,438 --> 01:14:12,268
you said mean things just as you do now,

742
01:14:12,648 --> 01:14:13,978
but you were happy.

743
01:14:17,653 --> 01:14:20,203
The man who taught you
how to write your name, Man-wol.

744
01:14:21,532 --> 01:14:23,532
Is he the person you miss the most

745
01:14:24,577 --> 01:14:25,787
in your past?

746
01:14:28,956 --> 01:14:30,496
How do you see...

747
01:14:32,919 --> 01:14:34,129
such things?

748
01:14:34,796 --> 01:14:36,416
Why do I see you?

749
01:14:37,048 --> 01:14:39,128
I'm scared
that I may have to pay the price for it.

750
01:14:42,887 --> 01:14:45,097
What's the sorrow you're still feeling?

751
01:14:45,681 --> 01:14:46,641
Maybe

752
01:14:47,725 --> 01:14:49,265
I'm here by your side...

753
01:14:50,895 --> 01:14:53,105
to help you get over that deep sorrow?

754
01:15:59,046 --> 01:16:01,006
You didn't die.

755
01:16:02,091 --> 01:16:03,971
You are tied to the Moon Tree,

756
01:16:04,051 --> 01:16:07,601
and the flow of life and death
has stopped for you. I told you that.

757
01:16:08,931 --> 01:16:12,691
The leaves sprout,
and the flowers bloom and wither.

758
01:16:13,185 --> 01:16:16,435
Your time will start flowing once again.

759
01:16:19,358 --> 01:16:20,898
The tree just changed.

760
01:16:22,612 --> 01:16:23,612
You're right.

761
01:16:25,031 --> 01:16:29,741
You might turn out to be someone
a lot more special than I thought.

762
01:16:48,221 --> 01:16:50,351
I can't just leave like this.

763
01:16:50,556 --> 01:16:53,096
What about my dog, Sun-dol?

764
01:16:53,184 --> 01:16:55,654
There's nothing you can do
when it comes to death.

765
01:16:55,728 --> 01:16:57,648
Gosh, I can't go!

766
01:16:57,730 --> 01:16:59,320
I can't go!

767
01:17:04,654 --> 01:17:06,324
Sun-dol, bark.

768
01:17:06,656 --> 01:17:08,196
You need to bark to live.

769
01:17:08,407 --> 01:17:10,157
If you don't, you'll die.

770
01:17:13,246 --> 01:17:14,866
My goodness, come on.

771
01:17:16,374 --> 01:17:19,254
Bark! You need to bark!

772
01:17:22,672 --> 01:17:24,882
It's been a week,
and he still won't budge.

773
01:17:25,174 --> 01:17:28,224
It's because he still has something
he's holding onto.

774
01:17:28,469 --> 01:17:32,269
At times like this, it's not
a bad idea to help him out a little.

775
01:17:38,854 --> 01:17:40,734
Sun-dol, you need to leave.

776
01:17:41,315 --> 01:17:44,395
Go outside! Hurry up and go!

777
01:17:44,485 --> 01:17:46,355
Will you please go outside?

778
01:17:47,571 --> 01:17:50,281
Just leave him.
He won't wander for too long.

779
01:17:50,491 --> 01:17:53,291
He'll find his way to Man-wol Inn.

780
01:17:53,369 --> 01:17:56,579
It's called Hotel del Luna now,
not Man-wol Inn.

781
01:17:56,664 --> 01:17:57,874
Yes, I forgot.

782
01:17:58,207 --> 01:18:00,667
Man-wol Inn, Man-wol Hostel,
and then Hotel del Luna.

783
01:18:00,918 --> 01:18:02,958
The name of that place
changes so frequently,

784
01:18:03,629 --> 01:18:06,589
but the owner of the place
hasn't changed at all.

785
01:18:06,924 --> 01:18:09,014
She hasn't changed for over 1,000 years.

786
01:18:09,593 --> 01:18:11,223
She has no hope.

787
01:18:11,721 --> 01:18:15,061
That's why I sent someone there.

788
01:18:16,892 --> 01:18:18,982
Are you going to change the owner?

789
01:18:20,479 --> 01:18:22,519
Man-wol's very stubborn,

790
01:18:22,606 --> 01:18:25,686
so I just sent her some help.

791
01:18:32,158 --> 01:18:34,238
Why did the tree change?

792
01:18:34,785 --> 01:18:37,115
Why do you think? It's because of you.

793
01:18:37,496 --> 01:18:38,706
It's because of me?

794
01:18:39,206 --> 01:18:41,456
The old memories that shriveled up

795
01:18:42,209 --> 01:18:44,169
crawled out again because of you.

796
01:18:44,670 --> 01:18:46,380
What did I do?

797
01:18:46,464 --> 01:18:49,884
All I did was tell you
about the dream I had of you.

798
01:18:49,967 --> 01:18:52,257
I know seeing ghosts is part of my job,

799
01:18:52,344 --> 01:18:54,474
but dreaming is not.

800
01:18:54,555 --> 01:18:58,385
I don't want to be treated unfairly
for something I never even asked for.

801
01:18:58,517 --> 01:19:00,767
You're going to get treated unfairly

802
01:19:02,396 --> 01:19:04,106
because you've already provoked me.

803
01:19:07,068 --> 01:19:09,398
The tree turned ugly because of you.

804
01:19:09,487 --> 01:19:11,567
I get that you're twisted,
but don't distort the truth.

805
01:19:12,573 --> 01:19:14,413
The tree looks alive and healthy.

806
01:19:14,492 --> 01:19:15,532
That is

807
01:19:16,619 --> 01:19:18,119
the problem.

808
01:19:19,955 --> 01:19:22,205
You just saved something
that shouldn't have been saved.

809
01:19:23,417 --> 01:19:25,207
Seeing that you're so angry,

810
01:19:25,586 --> 01:19:28,546
I guess my dream
really was about your past.

811
01:19:29,799 --> 01:19:31,929
Are you embarrassed that I saw your past?

812
01:19:33,928 --> 01:19:34,928
Yes.

813
01:19:35,805 --> 01:19:38,715
I'm extremely embarrassed right now.

814
01:19:40,226 --> 01:19:42,136
So I need to check this for myself.

815
01:19:49,485 --> 01:19:50,605
What are you doing?

816
01:19:57,535 --> 01:19:58,735
This is wrong.

817
01:19:59,245 --> 01:20:00,405
Stay still.

818
01:20:04,041 --> 01:20:05,171
Stop it.

819
01:20:05,793 --> 01:20:08,383
Chan-sung, let's sleep.

820
01:20:09,380 --> 01:20:10,380
Jang Man-won.

821
01:20:10,923 --> 01:20:13,013
You need to sleep
in order to have that dream.

822
01:20:13,092 --> 01:20:15,682
I need to check for myself
if you really saw me in a dream

823
01:20:16,137 --> 01:20:18,807
or if you're deceiving me
using all the rumors

824
01:20:19,265 --> 01:20:20,635
you heard in this hotel.

825
01:20:21,684 --> 01:20:24,064
Chan-sung, go to sleep.

826
01:20:25,396 --> 01:20:27,016
I can't fall asleep like this.

827
01:20:27,148 --> 01:20:29,278
And I can't guarantee
that I'll have that dream again

828
01:20:29,400 --> 01:20:30,860
even if I do fall asleep.

829
01:20:30,943 --> 01:20:33,743
Then sleep next to me
until you do have that dream.

830
01:20:35,698 --> 01:20:37,368
I don't want to sleep next to you.

831
01:20:37,450 --> 01:20:39,910
Be quiet and go to sleep
while I'm being nice.

832
01:20:42,455 --> 01:20:44,745
Fine. I'll sleep.

833
01:20:45,249 --> 01:20:47,249
You can sleep next to me
or watch me sleep.

834
01:20:47,334 --> 01:20:48,344
Do as you want.

835
01:20:50,629 --> 01:20:52,919
I'm going to kill you
if it turns out to be a lie.

836
01:20:53,007 --> 01:20:54,717
You just want it to be a lie

837
01:20:55,301 --> 01:20:56,971
because you don't like
that I saw your past.

838
01:20:58,721 --> 01:20:59,891
I'm not going to tell you

839
01:20:59,972 --> 01:21:01,852
what I see in my dreams
since you hate it so much.

840
01:21:01,932 --> 01:21:03,732
You can kill me or let me live.
Do as you want.

841
01:21:10,524 --> 01:21:12,034
Forget it. I'm not sleeping next to you.

842
01:21:37,885 --> 01:21:41,175
Do the memories that I revived
pain you that much?

843
01:21:43,349 --> 01:21:46,139
Because you can't stop thinking about him?

844
01:21:46,227 --> 01:21:48,937
Shut your mouth unless you want
to turn all green like the tree.

845
01:21:49,271 --> 01:21:50,481
Who is that man?

846
01:21:52,399 --> 01:21:53,399
Why do you ask?

847
01:21:54,360 --> 01:21:55,440
You think it might be you?

848
01:21:57,571 --> 01:22:00,411
Yes, that thought did occur to me.

849
01:22:00,991 --> 01:22:04,121
What I saw could be a memory
from my past life that I don't remember.

850
01:22:06,497 --> 01:22:08,667
There's no way you're him.

851
01:22:08,791 --> 01:22:09,671
Why?

852
01:22:10,501 --> 01:22:13,131
You've been on my mind
ever since I had that dream.

853
01:22:15,422 --> 01:22:18,382
You and I might go back a long way.

854
01:22:35,359 --> 01:22:36,279
You're not him.

855
01:22:37,528 --> 01:22:38,948
I feel nothing.

856
01:22:39,613 --> 01:22:42,373
If you were him,
I definitely wouldn't feel this way.

857
01:22:46,036 --> 01:22:47,286
That's a huge relief.

858
01:22:48,622 --> 01:22:51,712
I kept wondering, "What if I'm the man
she liked in the past?"

859
01:22:51,792 --> 01:22:53,132
It's been bothering me a lot.

860
01:22:54,920 --> 01:22:56,550
You didn't have feelings for him?

861
01:22:57,006 --> 01:22:58,626
You seemed to like him. A lot.

862
01:22:58,716 --> 01:23:00,466
A lot.

863
01:23:00,551 --> 01:23:01,641
Chan-sung.

864
01:23:02,678 --> 01:23:05,218
If you keep spewing useless nonsense,

865
01:23:05,306 --> 01:23:07,726
you'll get treated more unfairly.

866
01:23:07,850 --> 01:23:09,020
More unfairly? How?

867
01:23:09,101 --> 01:23:11,981
What? Are you not going to pay me?
I signed the contract though!

868
01:23:12,062 --> 01:23:13,062
Chan-sung!

869
01:23:15,399 --> 01:23:16,569
Starting today,

870
01:23:18,277 --> 01:23:19,697
you'll deal with ghost guests.

871
01:23:52,895 --> 01:23:55,055
How long has it been since--

872
01:24:00,069 --> 01:24:02,989
I guess you were lost for some time.
I'll help you with your check-in.

873
01:24:03,072 --> 01:24:05,662
I'll make sure you can use
our beauty and hair services first.

874
01:24:05,741 --> 01:24:07,701
This way, please. Let's take the elevator.

875
01:24:24,927 --> 01:24:28,257
What's going on? Is Ms. Jang still angry
even after drinking a case of champagne?

876
01:24:29,181 --> 01:24:32,061
I must've upset her somehow.
I think she's livid now.

877
01:24:35,270 --> 01:24:38,440
Well, what kind of sin
did Ms. Jang commit in the past?

878
01:24:38,982 --> 01:24:41,652
Does it have something to do
with a love affair?

879
01:24:42,694 --> 01:24:43,994
I'm not sure.

880
01:24:44,071 --> 01:24:47,281
Have you heard anything about a man
she's perhaps waiting for?

881
01:24:47,574 --> 01:24:48,914
No, nothing.

882
01:24:50,119 --> 01:24:51,119
Really?

883
01:24:59,253 --> 01:25:01,423
Is she not waiting for him?

884
01:25:01,713 --> 01:25:02,803
Mr. Koo.

885
01:25:03,257 --> 01:25:04,967
Are you concerned
about what she's thinking?

886
01:25:05,968 --> 01:25:07,588
No, not at all.

887
01:25:07,678 --> 01:25:09,508
She's not waiting
for the first and second choices.

888
01:25:09,596 --> 01:25:11,636
Who cares if you were the third one?
You're here now.

889
01:25:11,723 --> 01:25:12,773
Mr. Ji.

890
01:25:13,058 --> 01:25:15,888
I don't care at all
about what Ms. Jang thinks.

891
01:25:15,978 --> 01:25:17,938
Besides, I wasn't the third choice.

892
01:25:19,314 --> 01:25:21,654
I was the zeroth choice.
I beat everyone else.

893
01:25:21,942 --> 01:25:23,942
The zeroth choice? Sure.

894
01:25:24,027 --> 01:25:26,067
-I'm serious.
-Okay, you were the zeroth choice.

895
01:25:29,700 --> 01:25:33,250
It's all useless though.
She said she felt nothing.

896
01:25:35,747 --> 01:25:37,497
What's this spooky feeling?

897
01:25:37,749 --> 01:25:39,749
I think quite a number of guests
are coming.

898
01:25:40,252 --> 01:25:41,462
Will you be all right?

899
01:25:47,009 --> 01:25:48,049
No, I won't.

900
01:25:49,887 --> 01:25:53,887
When our guests first arrive,
they're often broken and ripped.

901
01:25:53,974 --> 01:25:56,274
Sometimes,
they have something tagging along.

902
01:25:56,643 --> 01:25:59,733
But all the guests here are groomed,
so you'll be fine.

903
01:26:04,526 --> 01:26:07,316
I'm now experienced enough
to handle this much.

904
01:26:10,199 --> 01:26:11,619
Can I get a refill on my coffee?

905
01:26:13,744 --> 01:26:14,954
We've run out of coffee beans.

906
01:26:15,037 --> 01:26:17,157
Please give us a moment.
We'll bring it to your table.

907
01:26:23,879 --> 01:26:25,799
How do you procure
the things that the guests

908
01:26:25,881 --> 01:26:27,221
eat and drink here?

909
01:26:27,674 --> 01:26:29,304
You can't get things delivered
from a store.

910
01:26:29,635 --> 01:26:31,215
We get them from the afterlife.

911
01:26:31,887 --> 01:26:35,387
When we treat our guests well
and help them go to the afterlife,

912
01:26:35,474 --> 01:26:37,144
we get compensated for our work.

913
01:26:37,226 --> 01:26:39,556
You mean, the ghosts pay you?

914
01:26:39,645 --> 01:26:41,855
They leave good energy behind.

915
01:26:42,064 --> 01:26:44,864
And that energy makes
the flowers in our garden bloom.

916
01:26:44,942 --> 01:26:48,112
The less regrets they take with them,
the more beautiful the flowers are.

917
01:26:48,946 --> 01:26:52,276
When our garden is filled with flowers,
Mago takes them

918
01:26:52,366 --> 01:26:55,986
and sends us the supplies
that we need in return.

919
01:26:58,080 --> 01:27:00,750
Then why does Ms. Jang

920
01:27:00,832 --> 01:27:02,962
need to earn money through the ghosts?

921
01:27:07,047 --> 01:27:08,837
It's all for her lavish lifestyle.

922
01:27:08,966 --> 01:27:11,636
She spends all the money
on her expensive champagnes,

923
01:27:11,718 --> 01:27:14,218
clothes, jewelry, and cars.

924
01:27:14,346 --> 01:27:16,966
How could someone who's being punished
have such an attitude?

925
01:27:21,103 --> 01:27:23,023
You said she's being punished.

926
01:27:24,064 --> 01:27:26,694
Someone told me
that I'm arrogant and foolish.

927
01:27:28,026 --> 01:27:29,316
Although I don't agree with it.

928
01:27:41,373 --> 01:27:43,083
I saw you in a dream.

929
01:27:45,502 --> 01:27:49,342
The leaves sprout,
and the flowers bloom and wither.

930
01:27:49,840 --> 01:27:53,220
The time of life and death
will flow once again.

931
01:27:55,888 --> 01:27:59,178
That wicked old hag is
pulling a silly trick on me.

932
01:28:02,936 --> 01:28:05,356
The man who taught you
how to write your name, Man-wol.

933
01:28:06,315 --> 01:28:08,225
Is he the person you miss the most

934
01:28:09,776 --> 01:28:10,776
in your past?

935
01:28:25,751 --> 01:28:26,921
Goodness.

936
01:28:28,837 --> 01:28:30,087
A slave ran away!

937
01:28:30,172 --> 01:28:32,012
Someone must've helped her. Find them.

938
01:28:33,050 --> 01:28:34,300
Who ran away?

939
01:29:54,006 --> 01:29:56,466
She's not here. Search outside.

940
01:30:01,930 --> 01:30:06,350
I heard the market where slaves
from Goguryeo are traded, was attacked.

941
01:30:06,768 --> 01:30:09,148
I had a feeling it might be you guys,
so I came to check.

942
01:30:10,188 --> 01:30:12,108
Thank goodness I'm nimble.

943
01:30:12,357 --> 01:30:13,897
I almost got killed by your dagger.

944
01:30:17,696 --> 01:30:19,906
No, I saved you because I'm nimble.

945
01:30:21,950 --> 01:30:23,370
I'm much obliged,

946
01:30:24,995 --> 01:30:26,285
but what will you do about this?

947
01:30:27,330 --> 01:30:29,080
My face is very precious.

948
01:30:29,166 --> 01:30:30,326
How will you pay for this?

949
01:30:31,001 --> 01:30:32,041
Too bad.

950
01:30:32,919 --> 01:30:35,129
The young lady at the Yeongju Castle
adores your face.

951
01:30:35,839 --> 01:30:37,299
How will you seduce her from now on?

952
01:30:41,887 --> 01:30:44,637
Do you think she only adores my face?

953
01:30:49,269 --> 01:30:50,349
Don't be such a baby.

954
01:30:50,604 --> 01:30:53,324
Let go. Let go of me.

955
01:30:53,857 --> 01:30:54,977
I said, let go!

956
01:30:55,233 --> 01:30:58,033
Shut it! Get him over here at once.
What are you waiting for?

957
01:30:58,111 --> 01:30:59,031
Get up!

958
01:30:59,112 --> 01:31:01,412
You bastards, let go!

959
01:31:01,990 --> 01:31:02,990
Let go.

960
01:31:03,075 --> 01:31:04,075
Yeon-u.

961
01:31:05,285 --> 01:31:06,285
Yeon-u.

962
01:31:08,246 --> 01:31:10,956
Let go. Yeon-u. It's Yeon-u.

963
01:31:12,459 --> 01:31:13,499
Shut your mouth!

964
01:31:16,254 --> 01:31:17,804
If you get out, you'll get caught too.

965
01:31:19,883 --> 01:31:22,393
I give you my word.
I'll be sure to save him

966
01:31:22,636 --> 01:31:23,966
and bring him to you.

967
01:31:25,055 --> 01:31:26,095
I promise.

968
01:31:54,417 --> 01:31:55,457
Yeon-u.

969
01:31:59,047 --> 01:32:00,087
Easy.

970
01:32:09,182 --> 01:32:10,232
Yeon-u.

971
01:32:18,400 --> 01:32:19,400
Are you all right?

972
01:32:20,402 --> 01:32:21,402
I'm okay.

973
01:32:35,959 --> 01:32:38,799
You have been waiting for that person

974
01:32:39,254 --> 01:32:41,134
over this long period of time.

975
01:32:53,768 --> 01:32:54,768
It is...

976
01:32:56,688 --> 01:32:58,688
too green and too gaudy.

977
01:33:02,360 --> 01:33:03,650
It looks ridiculous.

978
01:33:40,732 --> 01:33:41,822
Yeon-u.

979
01:33:43,026 --> 01:33:44,606
One of them was Yeon-u.

980
01:33:46,154 --> 01:33:47,824
He was in Man-wol's gang.

981
01:34:07,133 --> 01:34:09,303
Are you selling those flowers?

982
01:34:09,386 --> 01:34:10,966
How much is it? I'd like to buy one.

983
01:34:11,805 --> 01:34:13,215
No, that's fine.

984
01:34:13,348 --> 01:34:15,678
I already gave yours.

985
01:34:24,234 --> 01:34:27,744
Your dad almost died,
trying to pluck a flower for you.

986
01:34:28,571 --> 01:34:32,661
Because of that incident, he stopped
stealing and lived a diligent life.

987
01:34:33,535 --> 01:34:36,785
And he also raised a great son like you.

988
01:34:38,915 --> 01:34:41,915
Flowers! Flowers are the best present
for birthdays.

989
01:34:42,168 --> 01:34:43,168
Flowers.

990
01:34:44,963 --> 01:34:46,173
Weren't you the lady...

991
01:34:47,507 --> 01:34:50,797
So how is it? How's working at the hotel?

992
01:34:51,678 --> 01:34:53,718
Did you set this up?

993
01:34:54,514 --> 01:34:58,184
All I did was open a path.

994
01:34:58,268 --> 01:35:01,438
Are you telling me that it wasn't
a coincidence he went to the hotel?

995
01:35:02,147 --> 01:35:05,317
I planted a tree, you know.

996
01:35:06,318 --> 01:35:09,488
Gosh, that tree has been growing
spiky branches

997
01:35:09,571 --> 01:35:12,451
and unwelcoming to the others.

998
01:35:12,824 --> 01:35:16,834
I want you to take good care of the tree.

999
01:35:18,496 --> 01:35:20,956
Okay? If you have a hard time
looking after the tree,

1000
01:35:21,875 --> 01:35:23,415
you can come find me.

1001
01:36:27,524 --> 01:36:30,534
TO THE SAMDO RIVER

1002
01:36:40,161 --> 01:36:41,581
TO HEAVEN

1003
01:36:44,833 --> 01:36:45,833
Excuse me.

1004
01:36:47,001 --> 01:36:48,041
Hold on.

1005
01:36:54,217 --> 01:36:55,087
Sir.

1006
01:36:59,889 --> 01:37:01,349
Sun-dol, you brat.

1007
01:37:01,432 --> 01:37:03,312
You shouldn't be here.

1008
01:37:04,602 --> 01:37:07,402
I can't take you with me. Okay?

1009
01:37:07,814 --> 01:37:09,654
You... Goodness.

1010
01:37:10,567 --> 01:37:13,697
Where I'm headed is not a place for you.

1011
01:37:20,326 --> 01:37:22,786
He died all alone.
It looks like it's been a few days.

1012
01:37:23,288 --> 01:37:25,708
The door was open.
Why didn't the dog come out?

1013
01:37:25,999 --> 01:37:27,129
That's strange.

1014
01:37:29,752 --> 01:37:32,762
You shouldn't follow me there.

1015
01:37:33,423 --> 01:37:36,763
My goodness, you poor thing. Goodness.

1016
01:37:37,302 --> 01:37:41,012
Okay. Let's go there together, okay?
We'll go together.

1017
01:37:57,947 --> 01:37:59,867
Mago plucks the flowers

1018
01:37:59,949 --> 01:38:02,489
and hands them out to the people
who are headed to their afterlife.

1019
01:38:03,119 --> 01:38:05,749
And the souls who leave
with Mago's farewells

1020
01:38:05,830 --> 01:38:07,710
go to a good place.

1021
01:38:09,167 --> 01:38:10,537
That lady earlier...

1022
01:38:12,003 --> 01:38:13,253
is Mago?

1023
01:38:17,550 --> 01:38:19,930
PHARMACY
11-28 YAKJAE-GOLMOKGIL, GYEONGDONG MARKET

1024
01:39:09,394 --> 01:39:10,444
What's that?

1025
01:39:16,442 --> 01:39:18,402
Chan-sung, come on out!

1026
01:39:19,487 --> 01:39:20,527
Chan-sung!

1027
01:39:28,496 --> 01:39:30,786
Chan-sung, here.
I bought the most amazing bread.

1028
01:39:31,582 --> 01:39:33,962
Someone saw a ghost
at a bakery I regularly go to.

1029
01:39:34,043 --> 01:39:36,803
A ghost kneaded the dough
for this bread, so I waited to buy it.

1030
01:39:38,089 --> 01:39:39,799
Sanchez, don't say stuff like that.

1031
01:39:39,882 --> 01:39:42,222
I don't want to hear about ghosts
even at my own home.

1032
01:39:42,760 --> 01:39:45,850
Hey, what if the ghost who made this
followed me home?

1033
01:39:49,642 --> 01:39:50,942
Why are you here?

1034
01:39:51,185 --> 01:39:52,435
Why are you here again?

1035
01:39:53,313 --> 01:39:55,773
Chan-sung, what are you doing?
You're scaring me.

1036
01:39:56,691 --> 01:39:58,861
There's no ghost here. It's just bread.

1037
01:39:59,235 --> 01:40:00,395
Did you follow him here?

1038
01:40:04,032 --> 01:40:05,202
Did you follow the bread?

1039
01:40:08,036 --> 01:40:10,826
Chan-sung, I apologize for my silly story.

1040
01:40:10,913 --> 01:40:12,543
Let's just eat the bread. Okay?

1041
01:40:12,623 --> 01:40:13,883
I'm good. You eat it.

1042
01:40:14,334 --> 01:40:16,134
I think I have to go back to work now.

1043
01:40:17,628 --> 01:40:21,758
Hey. How can I eat this bread
after what you said just now?

1044
01:40:48,910 --> 01:40:51,370
Seems like Mr. Third Choice
brought back a guest who went out.

1045
01:40:51,829 --> 01:40:54,829
She went out of here,
went to a bakery, and made bread.

1046
01:40:55,083 --> 01:40:56,963
She shouldn't have done
something like that.

1047
01:40:57,168 --> 01:41:00,878
She's the one that was supposed
to leave in a limousine today, right?

1048
01:41:01,172 --> 01:41:03,722
Yes, Mr. Koo went to Ms. Jang
to get her signature

1049
01:41:03,800 --> 01:41:05,970
for postponing the limousine reservation.

1050
01:41:06,386 --> 01:41:09,306
Did she want to have bread
before leaving this world?

1051
01:41:09,389 --> 01:41:11,849
She can't even eat bread
from this world anyway.

1052
01:41:11,933 --> 01:41:13,353
She should've called for room service.

1053
01:41:13,434 --> 01:41:15,104
Why did she go to a bakery?

1054
01:41:15,186 --> 01:41:18,686
Hyeon-jung, can't you pay better attention
to the guests coming and leaving?

1055
01:41:18,856 --> 01:41:20,776
Do you want to get on the bus
to the afterlife?

1056
01:41:21,150 --> 01:41:25,030
I had a big group of guests yesterday,
so I was swamped.

1057
01:41:25,321 --> 01:41:26,701
Do your job right.

1058
01:41:36,833 --> 01:41:37,883
That was mean.

1059
01:41:38,793 --> 01:41:41,633
Wasn't it? How can she tell me
to take the bus?

1060
01:41:41,796 --> 01:41:43,626
Yes, that was a harsh thing to say.

1061
01:41:43,756 --> 01:41:45,336
Why is she so on edge like that?

1062
01:41:46,092 --> 01:41:48,012
Oh, it will be the 25th soon.

1063
01:41:48,928 --> 01:41:51,758
It's that day already.
We'll pass through it safely, won't we?

1064
01:41:51,889 --> 01:41:52,889
We have to.

1065
01:41:52,974 --> 01:41:55,394
If what happened 42 years ago
happens again,

1066
01:41:55,601 --> 01:41:58,021
Ms. Choe will be
dragged to the afterlife for sure.

1067
01:42:09,907 --> 01:42:13,827
A ghost can't just go around this world
stirring up trouble.

1068
01:42:14,787 --> 01:42:16,287
She didn't do anything serious,

1069
01:42:16,372 --> 01:42:18,542
so tell her to go
to the other world as planned.

1070
01:42:18,708 --> 01:42:20,168
I want to change that reservation.

1071
01:42:20,960 --> 01:42:22,090
Please sign here.

1072
01:42:22,170 --> 01:42:23,170
RESERVATION CHANGE

1073
01:42:25,715 --> 01:42:27,505
There's someone she really wants to see.

1074
01:42:29,093 --> 01:42:31,183
Every single ghost has someone
that they want to see!

1075
01:42:33,347 --> 01:42:35,597
She wants to see that person
because she never saw him

1076
01:42:35,683 --> 01:42:36,933
when she was alive.

1077
01:42:37,852 --> 01:42:39,232
She was blind when she was alive.

1078
01:42:39,312 --> 01:42:41,942
How can she want to see the person
when she has never seen him?

1079
01:42:42,273 --> 01:42:43,733
She doesn't even know the name.

1080
01:42:43,816 --> 01:42:45,936
Why is she looking for someone
she doesn't even know?

1081
01:42:46,152 --> 01:42:47,362
Forget it and go.

1082
01:42:47,445 --> 01:42:48,565
Stop annoying me.

1083
01:42:49,155 --> 01:42:50,485
She says her hands remember.

1084
01:42:50,615 --> 01:42:52,775
If she holds the hands,
she can feel who it is.

1085
01:42:54,076 --> 01:42:55,826
That's some nonsense a ghost is spewing.

1086
01:42:56,037 --> 01:42:58,207
Go away!

1087
01:43:03,252 --> 01:43:05,002
Is what you said also nonsense then?

1088
01:43:06,339 --> 01:43:08,259
You said you can tell by your feelings.

1089
01:43:08,424 --> 01:43:10,224
That I'm definitely not that man.

1090
01:43:12,762 --> 01:43:14,262
Then you don't know either.

1091
01:43:16,349 --> 01:43:17,389
You are...

1092
01:43:22,730 --> 01:43:24,570
definitely not him.

1093
01:43:27,360 --> 01:43:30,740
I'm right then, so you should sign this.

1094
01:43:35,993 --> 01:43:36,993
Darn.

1095
01:44:03,938 --> 01:44:05,608
JANG MAN-WOL

1096
01:44:10,945 --> 01:44:13,105
I'll find her that person
and then send her off.

1097
01:44:13,197 --> 01:44:16,657
She is the first guest I brought,
so I want to send her off nicely.

1098
01:44:26,460 --> 01:44:28,380
Don't try to get money off her.

1099
01:44:28,462 --> 01:44:29,962
She doesn't have any.

1100
01:44:32,008 --> 01:44:34,088
Why are you doing something
that won't get you money?

1101
01:44:34,176 --> 01:44:36,596
You're being used by that ghost.

1102
01:44:37,013 --> 01:44:40,143
You're so weakhearted.
Such an easy target for ghosts.

1103
01:44:41,392 --> 01:44:42,442
You're right.

1104
01:44:42,852 --> 01:44:45,312
If I'd been tougher and held out,
I wouldn't have ended up here.

1105
01:44:45,938 --> 01:44:48,068
I regret that I'm such a weak human being

1106
01:44:48,149 --> 01:44:49,279
that you like so much.

1107
01:44:50,818 --> 01:44:52,988
-Are you being sarcastic?
-I'm saying it's my fate.

1108
01:44:54,280 --> 01:44:56,410
I don't regret bringing you in

1109
01:44:56,949 --> 01:44:58,659
and complicating your life.

1110
01:45:01,621 --> 01:45:04,081
Do you really think you did that?

1111
01:45:05,958 --> 01:45:07,788
They say, "You complicate your own life."

1112
01:45:08,461 --> 01:45:10,001
Maybe it wasn't you who dragged me here.

1113
01:45:10,087 --> 01:45:12,717
Maybe I was the one who pushed myself
into the place I felt drawn to.

1114
01:45:14,467 --> 01:45:15,377
Drink this.

1115
01:45:15,885 --> 01:45:18,425
You should drink as much water as alcohol,
so you won't feel dry.

1116
01:45:23,100 --> 01:45:24,600
I'll bring some bread when I come back.

1117
01:45:24,936 --> 01:45:26,686
The place we're visiting
is a famous bakery.

1118
01:45:27,438 --> 01:45:30,188
It's the place that comedian
Kim Jun-hyun visited.

1119
01:45:32,068 --> 01:45:33,238
Try the Eat At Once game.

1120
01:45:33,319 --> 01:45:35,859
Why are you being nice?
You're making me nervous.

1121
01:45:36,864 --> 01:45:38,374
Are you giving me poison nicely?

1122
01:45:39,283 --> 01:45:40,623
I'm trying to take care of you.

1123
01:45:40,868 --> 01:45:42,618
If I give you water and bread,

1124
01:45:43,079 --> 01:45:44,039
who knows?

1125
01:45:44,121 --> 01:45:47,121
Leaves have sprouted from the dry tree.
Maybe flowers might bloom.

1126
01:45:48,960 --> 01:45:49,880
Don't.

1127
01:45:49,961 --> 01:45:52,841
Do you think I'm some seedling
that sprouts when you give it water?

1128
01:45:54,507 --> 01:45:57,717
I'm an old tree that's been dry
for over a thousand years.

1129
01:45:58,302 --> 01:46:00,932
The tree has leaves now.
I think it will be worthwhile.

1130
01:46:01,013 --> 01:46:03,723
-Stop being weird!
-Am I bothering you?

1131
01:46:04,183 --> 01:46:06,813
You said you didn't feel anything.
I guess that's not true.

1132
01:46:12,817 --> 01:46:14,277
That stupid...

1133
01:46:14,902 --> 01:46:16,492
Hey, Chan-sung.

1134
01:46:17,488 --> 01:46:20,368
Don't do this. Don't come here anymore.

1135
01:46:20,449 --> 01:46:22,239
Why? I have work to do.

1136
01:46:22,410 --> 01:46:23,870
You don't have to come here.

1137
01:46:25,037 --> 01:46:26,037
I'll let you go.

1138
01:46:26,414 --> 01:46:27,924
I have nowhere to go now.

1139
01:46:28,040 --> 01:46:30,170
Because you made me
leave the last hotel like that,

1140
01:46:30,251 --> 01:46:31,791
they hate me. I can't go back there.

1141
01:46:31,877 --> 01:46:33,627
There are other hotels on the Forbes list.

1142
01:46:33,713 --> 01:46:36,423
They liked me when they didn't know
I can see ghosts.

1143
01:46:36,882 --> 01:46:37,842
Not anymore.

1144
01:46:38,342 --> 01:46:40,932
And you have no one else except for me.

1145
01:46:42,555 --> 01:46:43,635
You were the third choice.

1146
01:46:43,723 --> 01:46:45,733
There are two other candidates,
and they're better.

1147
01:46:45,933 --> 01:46:47,353
Oh, those two.

1148
01:46:47,768 --> 01:46:50,308
They're too tough and strong for this job.

1149
01:46:50,396 --> 01:46:53,646
You need an easy target for ghosts
like me.

1150
01:46:54,150 --> 01:46:55,650
Someone who can resolve their grudges.

1151
01:46:55,735 --> 01:46:57,855
Here, I'm the zeroth pick.

1152
01:46:59,989 --> 01:47:01,029
Chan-sung.

1153
01:47:02,283 --> 01:47:05,043
If you keep doing this,
I really won't like you.

1154
01:47:05,161 --> 01:47:07,201
Having you like me
because I'm not bothering you.

1155
01:47:07,329 --> 01:47:09,369
Having you not like me
because I'm bothering you.

1156
01:47:10,374 --> 01:47:11,544
I prefer the latter.

1157
01:47:12,334 --> 01:47:14,674
I'll accompany the guest outside.

1158
01:47:22,178 --> 01:47:24,718
He will keep on provoking me?

1159
01:47:26,265 --> 01:47:29,055
He thinks I'm a joke
because the tree has leaves now.

1160
01:48:07,973 --> 01:48:09,563
What kind of bread are you looking for?

1161
01:48:11,185 --> 01:48:14,185
The bread that you're baking now

1162
01:48:15,064 --> 01:48:17,074
smells so nice.

1163
01:48:27,952 --> 01:48:29,452
It's chestnut bread.

1164
01:48:37,044 --> 01:48:38,174
It's warm, right?

1165
01:48:38,504 --> 01:48:39,764
And fluffy.

1166
01:48:40,339 --> 01:48:42,299
I just baked it.

1167
01:48:42,758 --> 01:48:45,638
Every time I went there,
he held my hand warmly.

1168
01:48:46,387 --> 01:48:49,307
My heart was thumping so hard,
I was afraid he'd know how I felt.

1169
01:48:49,390 --> 01:48:51,390
So I never got to talk to him properly.

1170
01:49:00,151 --> 01:49:02,031
You don't know his face or his name.

1171
01:49:02,444 --> 01:49:04,664
But you will know for sure
when you hold his hand, right?

1172
01:49:07,658 --> 01:49:09,078
If you approach him with those hands,

1173
01:49:09,160 --> 01:49:11,120
you will only make him scared
and fail to hold him.

1174
01:49:15,666 --> 01:49:17,416
Shall I tell them the situation
and find out?

1175
01:49:21,463 --> 01:49:23,633
Okay, I will lend my body to you.

1176
01:49:37,188 --> 01:49:40,858
Wow, the bread here is the best.

1177
01:49:42,818 --> 01:49:43,858
Thank you.

1178
01:49:45,321 --> 01:49:48,491
You made the bread with this hand.
It's a great hand.

1179
01:50:00,502 --> 01:50:01,842
It's not him.

1180
01:50:04,757 --> 01:50:06,297
Can you recommend a cake?

1181
01:50:06,383 --> 01:50:07,933
What about this strawberry cake?

1182
01:50:08,052 --> 01:50:09,472
The chocolate cake looks good too.

1183
01:50:13,140 --> 01:50:14,850
There's cheesecake too.

1184
01:50:18,437 --> 01:50:19,607
They're all delicious.

1185
01:50:21,732 --> 01:50:24,242
There's only one left, so it must be him.

1186
01:50:25,986 --> 01:50:27,736
Can I save points here?

1187
01:50:28,030 --> 01:50:29,870
Yes, do you have our membership card?

1188
01:50:30,491 --> 01:50:31,701
I didn't bring it.

1189
01:50:31,992 --> 01:50:33,372
Tell me your phone number.

1190
01:50:34,411 --> 01:50:38,081
Zero, one, zero...

1191
01:50:46,507 --> 01:50:47,547
What's your problem?

1192
01:50:48,467 --> 01:50:51,847
-This guy has been acting strange.
-Who are you?

1193
01:50:51,929 --> 01:50:52,969
Well, I...

1194
01:50:55,516 --> 01:50:56,516
Chan-sung.

1195
01:50:57,393 --> 01:50:58,443
What are you doing?

1196
01:50:59,186 --> 01:51:00,186
Sanchez.

1197
01:51:01,105 --> 01:51:03,015
I'm sorry. It won't happen again.

1198
01:51:04,900 --> 01:51:05,940
I'm sorry.

1199
01:51:06,860 --> 01:51:07,990
Take care.

1200
01:51:13,200 --> 01:51:14,200
What did you tell them?

1201
01:51:14,285 --> 01:51:17,155
I told them you're not a weirdo
and said sorry.

1202
01:51:17,246 --> 01:51:19,366
They said you should
never come here again.

1203
01:51:20,916 --> 01:51:22,246
I'm sorry, Sanchez.

1204
01:51:24,003 --> 01:51:25,133
Why did you do that?

1205
01:51:25,212 --> 01:51:27,672
I thought you went to the hotel.
Why are you here?

1206
01:51:27,756 --> 01:51:29,716
A guest asked me
to look for someone there.

1207
01:51:29,800 --> 01:51:30,840
Jeez.

1208
01:51:30,926 --> 01:51:32,636
You could've just asked for the name

1209
01:51:32,720 --> 01:51:35,430
instead of kneading the hands
of all the employees.

1210
01:51:36,640 --> 01:51:37,810
I had my reasons.

1211
01:51:39,601 --> 01:51:42,061
You should've asked me for help.

1212
01:51:42,438 --> 01:51:43,808
I'm a regular customer here.

1213
01:51:46,859 --> 01:51:48,779
Do you remember
every employee who worked here?

1214
01:51:48,861 --> 01:51:50,031
Of course I do.

1215
01:51:52,489 --> 01:51:53,529
Let go.

1216
01:51:58,787 --> 01:52:00,787
Am I the only one who sees

1217
01:52:00,873 --> 01:52:02,923
these green things?

1218
01:52:03,042 --> 01:52:04,172
Leaves have sprouted

1219
01:52:04,877 --> 01:52:06,247
on the tree.

1220
01:52:07,338 --> 01:52:09,468
It's so beautiful. Let's take a photo.

1221
01:52:09,548 --> 01:52:12,468
We shouldn't be marveling but lamenting.

1222
01:52:12,926 --> 01:52:15,176
It's a sign
that the hotel will face hardship.

1223
01:52:15,512 --> 01:52:16,352
Why is that?

1224
01:52:16,430 --> 01:52:19,310
Man-wol is being punished
by being tied to this tree.

1225
01:52:19,391 --> 01:52:22,521
Such changes to the tree must mean
that her punishment is coming to an end.

1226
01:52:22,603 --> 01:52:24,363
What's so wrong with that?

1227
01:52:24,438 --> 01:52:26,438
Think about what will happen
after she leaves.

1228
01:52:26,523 --> 01:52:29,193
We're still here thanks to her,
so what will happen to us?

1229
01:52:29,276 --> 01:52:31,356
We'll have to take
the bus to the afterlife.

1230
01:52:32,529 --> 01:52:33,489
No way.

1231
01:52:33,739 --> 01:52:35,239
I can't leave yet.

1232
01:52:35,324 --> 01:52:36,744
Same here.

1233
01:52:36,950 --> 01:52:38,830
Why did this suddenly happen?

1234
01:52:38,911 --> 01:52:40,251
What changed?

1235
01:52:41,580 --> 01:52:44,460
We have a new manager.

1236
01:52:50,506 --> 01:52:53,376
I guess Mr. Third Choice has something
to do with this.

1237
01:53:02,393 --> 01:53:05,563
The person you're looking for is
working here now.

1238
01:53:06,021 --> 01:53:08,361
Hello, here's the coffee you ordered.

1239
01:53:08,440 --> 01:53:09,530
That's him.

1240
01:53:09,775 --> 01:53:12,355
It tastes better
if you stir thoroughly. Enjoy.

1241
01:53:12,444 --> 01:53:13,534
Thank you.

1242
01:53:16,573 --> 01:53:17,783
Would you like to hold his hand?

1243
01:53:24,498 --> 01:53:25,418
Excuse me.

1244
01:53:26,291 --> 01:53:27,131
Yes?

1245
01:53:27,209 --> 01:53:30,459
Hello, I was a regular customer
of the bakery you worked at.

1246
01:53:32,297 --> 01:53:34,467
Oh, I see.

1247
01:53:35,217 --> 01:53:37,547
I hope you come by here often too.

1248
01:54:12,546 --> 01:54:13,666
It's warm, right?

1249
01:54:14,173 --> 01:54:15,473
And fluffy.

1250
01:54:17,217 --> 01:54:19,087
I just baked it.

1251
01:54:45,621 --> 01:54:47,661
Spend some time here
and come back to the hotel.

1252
01:55:04,932 --> 01:55:05,972
Do you feel proud?

1253
01:55:12,814 --> 01:55:13,774
It was worth it.

1254
01:55:15,275 --> 01:55:17,945
Is this a new car?

1255
01:55:18,362 --> 01:55:21,162
Yes, isn't it sweet?

1256
01:55:21,782 --> 01:55:24,122
The tacky poop color is not fit for a car.

1257
01:55:24,201 --> 01:55:26,041
Bright color like this is better.

1258
01:55:26,328 --> 01:55:27,828
So you went ahead and bought one?

1259
01:55:27,913 --> 01:55:29,923
No, but I call dibs.

1260
01:55:32,543 --> 01:55:34,803
Count me out
if you're off to buy one right now.

1261
01:55:35,629 --> 01:55:37,299
I'd rather get some sleep.

1262
01:55:37,381 --> 01:55:38,721
Sure, let's go sleep.

1263
01:55:39,841 --> 01:55:40,681
Sorry?

1264
01:55:41,426 --> 01:55:42,546
Let's sleep together.

1265
01:55:42,636 --> 01:55:44,886
I'm going to see how you dream this time.

1266
01:55:44,972 --> 01:55:49,232
As my boss, saying you'd like to
sleep with me is inappropriate.

1267
01:55:49,434 --> 01:55:50,774
I'll let it slide just this once.

1268
01:55:50,852 --> 01:55:52,272
Would you rather get a bite to eat?

1269
01:55:52,354 --> 01:55:55,074
I never said I wouldn't sleep.
I'm just not sleeping with you.

1270
01:55:55,148 --> 01:55:57,728
That's not what I said.
I only asked you out for a meal.

1271
01:55:57,818 --> 01:56:00,238
Do you realize that
you're not making any sense?

1272
01:56:00,904 --> 01:56:02,034
You said you'd look after me.

1273
01:56:02,114 --> 01:56:04,284
Seeing that I sleep and eat well is
how you do it.

1274
01:56:04,366 --> 01:56:05,236
Chan-sung.

1275
01:56:06,368 --> 01:56:07,538
Look after me.

1276
01:56:14,876 --> 01:56:16,166
What would you like to eat?

1277
01:56:32,519 --> 01:56:34,519
This place is quite famous
on social media.

1278
01:56:34,688 --> 01:56:36,058
I wanted to try the food.

1279
01:56:36,231 --> 01:56:37,321
You knew, right?

1280
01:56:38,483 --> 01:56:40,443
You knew that this is my friend's place.

1281
01:56:40,986 --> 01:56:42,606
Will you believe me if I say no?

1282
01:56:42,696 --> 01:56:44,406
Why ask when you're not going to?

1283
01:56:44,698 --> 01:56:45,738
What's good here?

1284
01:56:45,824 --> 01:56:48,164
Why ask when you won't even order
what I recommend?

1285
01:56:48,827 --> 01:56:49,697
You know me well.

1286
01:56:50,746 --> 01:56:53,116
I'll have this.

1287
01:56:53,874 --> 01:56:56,214
You'll have this. I want to try them both.

1288
01:56:57,169 --> 01:56:58,169
Chan-sung!

1289
01:57:01,590 --> 01:57:03,880
Sanchez is my roommate.

1290
01:57:03,967 --> 01:57:05,337
He gets scared easily,

1291
01:57:05,427 --> 01:57:07,427
so don't mention anything about ghosts.

1292
01:57:08,597 --> 01:57:11,517
You must've lied to Sanchez
about where you work.

1293
01:57:13,477 --> 01:57:14,767
-Hi, Sanchez.
-Hey.

1294
01:57:14,978 --> 01:57:16,648
Did you find the man you were looking for?

1295
01:57:16,730 --> 01:57:17,810
Yes, thanks to you.

1296
01:57:19,232 --> 01:57:21,572
So this is my colleague.

1297
01:57:22,527 --> 01:57:24,697
She must be a hotelier too.

1298
01:57:24,780 --> 01:57:25,950
That's so cool.

1299
01:57:26,406 --> 01:57:28,026
We'll order number 2 and number 15.

1300
01:57:28,116 --> 01:57:29,736
Sure thing. Let's see.

1301
01:57:30,243 --> 01:57:31,753
It's a hard place to work at, isn't it?

1302
01:57:32,996 --> 01:57:36,116
Chan-sung's been stressed out
ever since he started to work there.

1303
01:57:37,125 --> 01:57:39,665
You said the owner was a maniac, right?

1304
01:57:40,087 --> 01:57:41,127
That lady...

1305
01:57:41,254 --> 01:57:42,674
What was her name again?

1306
01:57:42,964 --> 01:57:44,884
-Jang Man-wol.
-Yes, Jang Man-wol.

1307
01:57:45,300 --> 01:57:47,590
I remember because the name is so weird.

1308
01:57:47,969 --> 01:57:49,849
Anyway, from what I hear,

1309
01:57:49,930 --> 01:57:53,140
employees must badmouth their bosses
to relieve stress at work.

1310
01:57:53,225 --> 01:57:54,885
So when I serve the pizza,

1311
01:57:54,976 --> 01:57:56,766
think of it as that owner's head.

1312
01:57:56,978 --> 01:57:59,938
And enjoy your meal
while ripping her apart.

1313
01:58:00,023 --> 01:58:01,943
Rip, bite, and chew, all right?

1314
01:58:09,074 --> 01:58:11,954
It'll take more than one pizza
to vent all your anger.

1315
01:58:12,702 --> 01:58:13,832
Order another one.

1316
01:58:15,497 --> 01:58:17,577
I never called you a maniac.

1317
01:58:17,666 --> 01:58:20,036
I only said you were hard to reason with.

1318
01:58:20,210 --> 01:58:21,380
What's so wrong about it?

1319
01:58:21,461 --> 01:58:24,011
Don't we all get a little crazy sometimes?

1320
01:58:26,842 --> 01:58:28,642
Anyway, this reminds me

1321
01:58:29,219 --> 01:58:32,679
of the loaf of bread
you promised to get me.

1322
01:58:35,559 --> 01:58:36,979
How did it go at the bakery?

1323
01:58:37,811 --> 01:58:38,941
It all went well.

1324
01:58:39,020 --> 01:58:41,360
Her hands guided her to the right place.

1325
01:58:42,315 --> 01:58:43,355
Is that so?

1326
01:58:44,651 --> 01:58:46,991
But the memories
that ghosts have can get...

1327
01:58:48,905 --> 01:58:50,315
all mixed up sometimes.

1328
01:58:51,450 --> 01:58:53,790
Floating around so for long

1329
01:58:54,161 --> 01:58:56,871
makes them forget what's important.

1330
01:59:03,712 --> 01:59:06,132
Sometimes, they only remember

1331
01:59:06,798 --> 01:59:08,218
what they want to remember.

1332
01:59:44,628 --> 01:59:46,878
You said
that she only remembered his hands.

1333
01:59:49,382 --> 01:59:51,302
That's a beautiful memory.

1334
01:59:54,429 --> 01:59:55,849
Still, it's missing something.

1335
01:59:56,723 --> 01:59:58,893
She lived a decently long life,

1336
01:59:59,017 --> 02:00:01,227
but his hand is
the only thing she desperately remembers

1337
02:00:01,895 --> 02:00:03,805
just because he kindly picked up
bread for her?

1338
02:00:07,859 --> 02:00:09,279
What are you getting at?

1339
02:00:09,653 --> 02:00:11,743
The most important memories for a ghost

1340
02:00:12,322 --> 02:00:13,702
are mostly the same.

1341
02:00:15,408 --> 02:00:16,828
The memories of when they died.

1342
02:01:01,871 --> 02:01:03,461
Help me.

1343
02:03:07,122 --> 02:03:08,422
Chan-sung.

1344
02:03:09,249 --> 02:03:10,999
Come to my hotel if you die.

1345
02:03:41,874 --> 02:03:43,584
Darn it. What's your problem?

1346
02:03:55,262 --> 02:03:57,682
If you do this,
you'll turn to ashes and disappear.

1347
02:03:57,765 --> 02:03:59,175
Don't leave in vain like that.

1348
02:04:02,895 --> 02:04:05,475
I'll make sure he gets punished
for what he did.

1349
02:04:05,981 --> 02:04:07,231
I promise!

1350
02:05:08,544 --> 02:05:12,594
You found the guy who committed
a hit-and-run six months ago?

1351
02:05:12,714 --> 02:05:15,594
So you caught him by yourself
and brought him here?

1352
02:05:15,676 --> 02:05:18,636
Yes, he hit a blind woman
who was crossing the street

1353
02:05:18,720 --> 02:05:21,220
with his motorcycle and ran away,
leaving her for dead.

1354
02:05:21,390 --> 02:05:22,720
Oh, really?

1355
02:05:23,100 --> 02:05:25,190
Gosh, you're incredible.

1356
02:05:26,478 --> 02:05:30,018
"He hit a blind woman
who was crossing the street..."

1357
02:06:03,473 --> 02:06:06,773
You're the first guest
I'm sending off at this hotel.

1358
02:06:07,644 --> 02:06:10,194
I heard you go to a nice place
if you receive that flower.

1359
02:06:11,732 --> 02:06:12,902
Thank you.

1360
02:06:13,650 --> 02:06:16,900
The memory I had of his hand
was a horrible one.

1361
02:06:17,696 --> 02:06:19,816
But I was a fool to remember it

1362
02:06:19,907 --> 02:06:21,947
as a warm and heart-fluttering memory.

1363
02:06:22,034 --> 02:06:24,544
That's because you were probably
the kind of person

1364
02:06:25,245 --> 02:06:28,115
who always tried to remember
happy memories

1365
02:06:29,041 --> 02:06:30,791
regardless of how small they were

1366
02:06:30,876 --> 02:06:33,456
over terrible hardships you had.

1367
02:07:05,035 --> 02:07:07,195
SAMDO RIVER

1368
02:07:46,576 --> 02:07:47,406
Sir.

1369
02:07:50,455 --> 02:07:52,165
Would you like some more coffee?

1370
02:08:25,157 --> 02:08:27,697
Isn't this place huge?

1371
02:08:33,874 --> 02:08:36,544
There's a sandy beach if you go outside.

1372
02:08:36,877 --> 02:08:38,337
Your son will love it.

1373
02:08:39,546 --> 02:08:40,506
Thank you.

1374
02:08:40,839 --> 02:08:42,129
Let's go have fun in the water.

1375
02:08:43,341 --> 02:08:44,431
Come on.

1376
02:08:48,263 --> 02:08:49,473
Do you want me to carry you?

1377
02:08:49,556 --> 02:08:51,976
There we go.

1378
02:08:53,310 --> 02:08:56,230
The father and son came together
due to a car accident.

1379
02:09:02,527 --> 02:09:04,527
Gi-ung, stop!

1380
02:09:06,239 --> 02:09:08,029
Gi-ung, no!

1381
02:09:22,881 --> 02:09:25,681
He still hasn't come to his senses
even after what he saw.

1382
02:09:30,138 --> 02:09:31,138
Ms. Jang.

1383
02:09:32,432 --> 02:09:34,232
We saw the tree in the garden.

1384
02:09:35,393 --> 02:09:37,313
Everyone's feeling very nervous.

1385
02:09:49,991 --> 02:09:53,791
The tree's been dead for over 1,000 years.
Why did it suddenly come back to life?

1386
02:09:53,870 --> 02:09:56,500
Mago told me
that someone will come and help me leave.

1387
02:09:56,998 --> 02:09:58,328
I guess that person's here.

1388
02:09:58,416 --> 02:10:00,456
Is that person Mr. Koo?

1389
02:10:00,961 --> 02:10:01,841
Yes.

1390
02:10:01,920 --> 02:10:03,840
What did Mr. Koo say?

1391
02:10:03,922 --> 02:10:05,632
He told me that he'll take care of me

1392
02:10:05,715 --> 02:10:08,585
and that he'll try to make flowers
bloom along with the leaves.

1393
02:10:10,095 --> 02:10:11,465
I guess I'll be gone

1394
02:10:12,430 --> 02:10:13,720
once the flowers fall.

1395
02:10:13,807 --> 02:10:16,267
Then what about us?
What's going to happen to us?

1396
02:10:17,102 --> 02:10:18,602
How would I know?

1397
02:10:18,895 --> 02:10:20,605
That's up to you.

1398
02:10:20,939 --> 02:10:23,729
We can give up all together
and move onto the afterlife.

1399
02:10:23,817 --> 02:10:26,027
Or you can roam around
this world as vengeful ghosts

1400
02:10:26,111 --> 02:10:27,451
and turn into ashes.

1401
02:10:28,447 --> 02:10:29,567
Suit yourself.

1402
02:10:29,656 --> 02:10:32,116
We must stay at the hotel a little longer.

1403
02:10:32,576 --> 02:10:34,406
And you can't leave just yet either.

1404
02:10:35,996 --> 02:10:39,036
We should let go of Mr. Koo.
Besides, he was our third choice,

1405
02:10:39,124 --> 02:10:41,004
and we have the fourth candidate ready.

1406
02:10:42,794 --> 02:10:45,384
Hey. Isn't that too harsh?

1407
02:10:49,009 --> 02:10:50,719
Don't distract me and go away.

1408
02:10:50,969 --> 02:10:51,929
I'm sorry.

1409
02:10:52,012 --> 02:10:53,052
We'll go away.

1410
02:10:53,180 --> 02:10:54,470
What's gotten into her?

1411
02:10:54,556 --> 02:10:55,596
What's her deal?

1412
02:10:55,682 --> 02:10:56,892
Let's just go.

1413
02:10:56,975 --> 02:10:58,265
She's unbelievable.

1414
02:11:03,148 --> 02:11:06,938
A ghost has taken up her body.
And she's bold too. She's the perfect fit.

1415
02:11:09,946 --> 02:11:11,656
Right. We have another candidate.

1416
02:11:12,449 --> 02:11:15,789
I helped her steal the body,
so I can definitely use that against her.

1417
02:11:16,786 --> 02:11:18,616
Besides, her family is loaded too.

1418
02:11:18,830 --> 02:11:20,250
Let's let go of Mr. Koo.

1419
02:11:21,708 --> 02:11:22,998
He won't leave.

1420
02:11:23,335 --> 02:11:25,545
I told him to leave, but he said no.

1421
02:11:25,629 --> 02:11:27,759
Koo Chan-sung can see ghosts now.

1422
02:11:27,839 --> 02:11:28,879
And he's settling in too.

1423
02:11:28,965 --> 02:11:30,965
Even if I kick him out
with his eyes carved out,

1424
02:11:31,468 --> 02:11:33,088
he'll see ghosts and the hotel.

1425
02:11:33,178 --> 02:11:36,518
Mago will be able to take away
his ability to see the ghosts.

1426
02:11:37,557 --> 02:11:40,727
You think that old hag will do me a favor?
She's the one who sent him to me.

1427
02:11:41,811 --> 02:11:43,061
We can't kill a human,

1428
02:11:43,146 --> 02:11:45,016
but if we let him be,
we'll have to get on the bus.

1429
02:11:45,106 --> 02:11:47,226
There's a way to fix this
without killing him.

1430
02:11:49,110 --> 02:11:50,530
The guest...

1431
02:11:52,572 --> 02:11:54,822
who's staying in Room 13.

1432
02:11:58,078 --> 02:11:59,868
The guest in Room 13...

1433
02:12:16,179 --> 02:12:20,139
The guest in Room 13 hates
even the sound of a human's breath.

1434
02:12:22,185 --> 02:12:24,805
If a human sees the guest in Room 13,

1435
02:12:25,689 --> 02:12:26,769
the human will go crazy.

1436
02:12:26,856 --> 02:12:30,066
Are you suggesting
that we make him go mad?

1437
02:12:34,281 --> 02:12:35,281
Yes.

1438
02:12:36,324 --> 02:12:39,334
If he goes crazy
and roams around like a madman,

1439
02:12:40,078 --> 02:12:42,288
he won't be able to come here
even though he sees ghosts.

1440
02:12:42,372 --> 02:12:45,212
This world would isolate such people
without our involvement.

1441
02:12:45,292 --> 02:12:46,792
Mental institution.

1442
02:12:47,669 --> 02:12:50,049
Ms. Jang, do you approve of this?

1443
02:13:01,683 --> 02:13:03,313
Where is Koo Chan-sung now?

1444
02:13:39,429 --> 02:13:43,599
This punk keeps making my garden
look more and more hideous.

1445
02:13:52,567 --> 02:13:55,317
No one told you to chase around a ghost
without getting any sleep.

1446
02:13:55,737 --> 02:13:58,157
You don't have much time left
as a sane man.

1447
02:13:58,281 --> 02:14:00,621
It looks like you're wasting
your precious time sleeping.

1448
02:14:07,916 --> 02:14:08,916
What a shame.

1449
02:14:09,542 --> 02:14:10,842
But it's all your fault.

1450
02:14:11,211 --> 02:14:13,341
You were really my cup of tea,

1451
02:14:14,214 --> 02:14:15,924
but I hate that you can look into me.

1452
02:14:35,777 --> 02:14:36,857
Why are you smiling?

1453
02:14:37,487 --> 02:14:39,237
Did you come here,
so we could sleep together?

1454
02:14:39,698 --> 02:14:41,318
Are you happy
now that you watched me sleep?

1455
02:14:43,159 --> 02:14:44,489
You saw me in your dream again?

1456
02:14:44,786 --> 02:14:45,866
Do you want to know?

1457
02:14:47,330 --> 02:14:48,920
Sit down. I'll tell you

1458
02:14:49,541 --> 02:14:51,291
what you were like in my dream.

1459
02:14:56,631 --> 02:14:58,261
This is what I hate.

1460
02:14:59,050 --> 02:15:02,260
I should be saying that I'll rip
your mouth open if you don't shut up.

1461
02:15:03,430 --> 02:15:07,770
But for a second, I thought about
sitting down there. And I really hate it.

1462
02:15:10,687 --> 02:15:12,897
You haven't budged an inch
for over 1,000 years.

1463
02:15:13,648 --> 02:15:15,148
A second means a lot.

1464
02:15:15,692 --> 02:15:18,822
Yes, this change means a lot to me,

1465
02:15:19,696 --> 02:15:21,986
and you'll have to pay for it.

1466
02:15:22,699 --> 02:15:24,949
You agreed that you're the one
who complicated your own life.

1467
02:15:25,452 --> 02:15:28,252
Whatever happens to you,
it's all your fault.

1468
02:15:31,499 --> 02:15:34,039
If something happens to me,
I'm sure you'll protect me.

1469
02:15:37,505 --> 02:15:41,005
You said you were going to protect me
as I'm a weak human.

1470
02:15:45,013 --> 02:15:47,143
You were the one
who stopped the motorcycle.

1471
02:15:48,475 --> 02:15:51,385
No, I didn't. I couldn't care less.

1472
02:15:52,103 --> 02:15:53,693
I know that it was you.

1473
02:15:53,938 --> 02:15:55,478
I jumped in because I trusted you.

1474
02:15:55,857 --> 02:15:57,227
I said, it wasn't me.

1475
02:15:57,317 --> 02:15:59,937
I trust that you will protect me.

1476
02:16:01,571 --> 02:16:04,491
So please protect me
if something happens to me.

1477
02:16:05,909 --> 02:16:07,699
I will stay right next to you.

1478
02:16:10,747 --> 02:16:12,417
I'm going to kick you out.

1479
02:17:48,011 --> 02:17:49,641
Did it come from the dream?

1480
02:17:50,972 --> 02:17:52,602
That second of Man-wol?

1481
02:18:06,696 --> 02:18:07,736
Mr. Koo.

1482
02:18:08,114 --> 02:18:10,454
I need your help with a guest.

1483
02:18:11,159 --> 02:18:13,369
Okay. Which room is the guest in?

1484
02:18:14,871 --> 02:18:18,631
It's Room 13.
She's a long-term stay guest.

1485
02:18:26,633 --> 02:18:29,143
Burn this incense stick in Room 13.

1486
02:18:29,844 --> 02:18:31,224
Okay, I'll do that.

1487
02:18:32,597 --> 02:18:34,307
The guest is very picky.

1488
02:18:34,390 --> 02:18:36,350
I'm sorry for troubling you.

1489
02:18:39,562 --> 02:18:41,942
I'm getting used to ghost guests now.

1490
02:18:42,231 --> 02:18:43,401
Don't worry.

1491
02:18:58,498 --> 02:18:59,578
I'm sorry.

1492
02:19:00,583 --> 02:19:03,423
I feel like I'm giving up
on my virtue as a scholar.

1493
02:19:04,003 --> 02:19:05,343
I'm ashamed.

1494
02:19:06,381 --> 02:19:08,301
I liked him. He was like a good friend.

1495
02:19:33,574 --> 02:19:36,494
Mr. Koo is

1496
02:19:37,662 --> 02:19:40,082
on his way to Room 13 now.

1497
02:23:24,180 --> 02:23:26,270
Where is the guest?

1498
02:24:15,314 --> 02:24:16,324
Chan-sung!

1499
02:24:21,404 --> 02:24:22,494
Don't look.

1500
02:24:27,243 --> 02:24:28,793
Don't let her hear your breathing.

1501
02:24:35,751 --> 02:24:37,171
But I hear--

1502
02:24:37,878 --> 02:24:38,838
Don't listen to it.

1503
02:24:43,843 --> 02:24:44,973
What's the matter?

1504
02:26:50,719 --> 02:26:53,309
Chan-sung isn't going anywhere.
I'm keeping him by my side.

1505
02:26:53,389 --> 02:26:55,179
You sent me to that room
on purpose, didn't you?

1506
02:26:55,266 --> 02:26:57,056
I lost one of the earrings.

1507
02:26:57,309 --> 02:26:58,979
You'll go bankrupt at this rate.

1508
02:26:59,061 --> 02:27:01,111
Be kind and cut down on your spending.

1509
02:27:02,857 --> 02:27:04,647
She's being forced into a marriage.

1510
02:27:04,733 --> 02:27:06,153
You think this is the front desk?

1511
02:27:06,235 --> 02:27:08,145
Ma'am, you can't do this to our employee.

1512
02:27:08,237 --> 02:27:10,357
-I am okay with it.
-Gosh.

1513
02:27:10,489 --> 02:27:12,069
Please take it.

1514
02:27:12,158 --> 02:27:14,368
You'll actually marry her?

1515
02:27:14,743 --> 02:27:16,083
Jang Man-wol...

1516
02:27:16,370 --> 02:27:17,870
Do you love me too?

1517
02:27:18,247 --> 02:27:20,247
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu
